	quest.008D186B4E0ED14F.quest_desc: [
		"The Steam Oven is another machine that uses Steam for something useful. \\n\\nBy putting Steam into the Steam Oven it will act as a furnace to any items in it. Making Ingots from Ores and cooking food items. \\n\\nIt's a 2x2x2 machine of Steam Oven blocks."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_oven.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.00DC2BA6CFAA1F8B.quest_desc: ["Fishing loot."]
	quest.01B13BBB41BBB460.quest_desc: [
		"When encased in a complete set of &cUtherium Armor&r, a vanguard commander commands a defensive fortification that stands as an absolute equal to the legendary, blast-resistant strength of refined netherite plating. "
		""
		"The dense, volatile matrix of the alloy absorbs monumental kinetic impacts, protecting the wearer from catastrophic trauma on the front lines of battle. "
		""
		"Remarkably, this supreme level of protection completely defies standard modern metallurgy. "
		""
		"It bypasses the tedious requirement of an ancient Smithing Template entirely, allowing an artisan to shape the raw plates directly upon a standard anvil and instantly unlock the pinnacle of defensive martial engineering."
	]
	quest.01B13BBB41BBB460.title: "&cUtherium&r Armor"
	quest.01F18150EC923482.quest_desc: [
		"To initiate the mass matter-digitization of a colony's stockpile, an engineer must forge the foundational apparatus of the network: the &3Controller&r. "
		""
		"This device functions as the absolute core of the &3Refined Storage&r grid, serving as the central nervous system for all interconnected sorting arrays. "
		""
		"In its dormant state, it rests as an inert block of cold circuitry; however, when supplied with a constant stream of external energy, it breathes immediate vitality into every conduit, drive, and terminal linked to its matrix, binding them into a single, unified digital collective."
	]
	quest.01F18150EC923482.quest_subtitle: "Section I: The Foundation of Digital Inherent Systems"
	quest.01F18150EC923482.title: "Data Log: Network Initialization"
	quest.020E6AF37A0421C8.quest_desc: [
		"The Water Tank is like having a barrel outside. Just this barrel is much bigger. It collects water and can hold water for Steam Locomotives. \\n\\nThe amount of water is makes is dependent on the biome and visible to the sky. \\n\\nIt's made by a 3x3x3 Water Tank blocks with the center being hollow."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_tank.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.030E1901DF02E65F.quest_desc: [
		"Manually hauling and cataloging loose chalk variants, tallow candles, calcified skulls, and attuned crystals for every geometric layout creates severe logistical clutter in your field inventory. To streamline your construction workflows, you must fabricate a specialized Ritual Satchel."
		""
		"By executing a sneak-right-click action while holding the satchel in your hand, you can open its internal storage matrix to load it with all necessary ritual construction supplies."
		""
		"Once your inventory is stored, simply right-click any active holographic preview block generated by your guidebook. The satchel will interface with the projection, initiating a slow, automated assembly process that automatically draws and installs every required rune and decoration directly into the world."
		""
		"To monitor tool integrity without opening the GUI, observe the bag's visual state: if any internal chalk drop below 40% durability, the satchel's active enchantment glint will extinguish. This serves as a vital physical diagnostic signal indicating that your components require immediate repair or replacement."
	]
	quest.030E1901DF02E65F.quest_subtitle: "Advanced material loading and automated rune placement."
	quest.030E1901DF02E65F.title: "Automated Geometry: The Ritual Satchel"
	quest.032B654201E71618.quest_desc: ["These &cTrack Kits&r are for using entities with your &7Carts&r (Entities aka Mobs). \\n\\nThe &cEmbarking Kit&r will pick up any Mobs nearby and put them in a &7Cart&r. \\nThe &cDisembarking Kit&r unloads Mobs from the &7Carts&r. \\nThe &cDumping Kit&r will drop the mobs in the &7Carts&r below the &6tracks&r its on."]
	quest.035C52EF63AD23A7.quest_desc: ["Hence the name of the mod, &lRailCraft&r, and what it revolves around, &5Trains&r, &6Rails&r are pretty important. \\n\\nThe &2Vanilla&r ones work for lots of these but come on we all know they suck. Upgraded ones will need some more special items for their recipes! Craft them! (They might require using machines to make the items so check out that part of the quest!)"]
	quest.03C002E4A4515E0E.quest_desc: [
		"Spice of Life: Carrot Edition encourages players to eat many different kinds of food by rewarding them for trying new things. Each time you reach a goal for eating new foods, you gain extra hearts that permanently increase your maximum health."
		""
		"The Food Book shows which foods you have already eaten and helps you track your progress toward earning your next extra heart."
	]
	quest.03C002E4A4515E0E.quest_subtitle: "Craft the Food Book"
	quest.03C78165C5CBD9E1.title: "&a16k Storage Part"
	quest.0423D99FBFB5CB32.quest_subtitle: "Best Tool for Acquiring Sacrifical Meat!"
	quest.0423D99FBFB5CB32.title: "Tools of the Trade: Butcher's Knife"
	quest.0501F76E80B4BC31.quest_subtitle: "Bring your pickaxe along!"
	quest.0501F76E80B4BC31.title: "Small underground Mazes"
	quest.050D8480EE9D8E62.quest_desc: [
		"The Wigglewood Forests appear just like any other forests. "
		""
		"However, the trees here have a habit of wandering as they please."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_wiggle.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.050D8480EE9D8E62.title: "Wigglewood Forest"
	quest.05252B9E55232054.quest_desc: [
		"Utilizing the ultimate planar frequencies of &dRonaza's Contact&r, you can subject an existing &bIesnium Sacrificial Bowl&r to extreme extra-dimensional compression, permanently transmuting the block into the Eldritch Chalice."
		""
		"Installing this pinnacle artifact at the absolute geometric center of any pentacle completely shatters the baseline speed limits of occult geometry. The device acts as an immediate sub-spatial gateway, forcing the local fabric of reality to bypass traditional casting intervals and dimensional tearing delays entirely."
		""
		"Once active, every ceremony, summoning matrix, and material infusion initiated within the runic perimeter will complete instantly. Runic calculations, offering consumption, and entity manifestation happen in a single computational tick—allowing your facility to establish maximum-efficiency, hands-free automation loops with zero operational downtime."
	]
	quest.05252B9E55232054.quest_subtitle: "Eliminating dimensional tearing latency through supreme sub-spatial channels."
	quest.05252B9E55232054.title: "Instantaneous Breach: The Eldritch Chalice"
	quest.052980924E1F11B4.quest_subtitle: "These rare creatures can withstand the fall from any height, but still need to be taken care off well."
	quest.05369F8F4DF5A5BA.quest_desc: [
		"Reaching this milestone marks the complete assembly of your extra-dimensional manufacturing toolkit. While your structured progression path through this chapter is finalized, your integration of these arcane sciences is only just beginning."
		""
		"To transition your temporary workshop into a permanent, automated industrial center, consider prioritizing the following facility optimizations:"
		""
		"&l&o&nComprehensive Schematic Audit&r: Consult your &6Dictionary of Spirits&r to review the full, unrestricted catalog of unlisted auxiliary recipes, niche transmutes, and utility constructs to discover new material optimization routes for your factory floor."
		""
		"&l&o&nDedicated Perimeter Zoning&r: If you are still operating out of a temporary layout, finalize your infrastructure by constructing three separate, heavily decorated 19x19 ritual zones. Separating your Summoning, Possession, and Infusion matrices permanently prevents block overlap errors and streamlines your automation pipeline."
		""
		"&l&o&nCross-Mod Logistics Hookups&r: Link your newly manufactured endgame assets—such as the high-output crushing circuits and infinite miners—directly into your centralized storage and automated crafting networks to completely eliminate all remaining resource bottlenecks."
		""
		"The veil has been thoroughly shattered, and the laws of the Otherworld are entirely yours to dictate."
	]
	quest.05369F8F4DF5A5BA.quest_subtitle: "Maximizing the full operational potential of your established occult network."
	quest.05369F8F4DF5A5BA.title: "Absolute Mastery: The Path Forward"
	quest.05839D9537FA2FDD.quest_desc: [
		"Step 4: Tavern"
		""
		"Your colonists will need a place to sleep and a house, so it is recommended to build a Tavern next. The Tavern also allows visitors to come to your colony, and you can recruit them to stay as citizens."
	]
	quest.0594025A747665CF.quest_desc: [
		"Utilizing the ultimate cosmic frequencies of &dRonaza's Contact&r, you can permanently restructure your standard containment equipment, upgrading a base Soul Gem into a pristine Trinity Gem.This elite apparatus represents the absolute zenith of biological capture technology, featuring an overhauled resonance grid that significantly expands your logistical capabilities:"
		""
		"&l&o&nMassive Variable Capture&r: The device easily overpowers and siphons high-density, large-scale entities that completely resist lower-tier containment cells—allowing you to easily transport massive livestock, elite monstrous guards, and high-health sacrificial catalysts across dimensions."
		""
		"&l&o&nPlanar Boundaries&r: Note that while the gem's energetic fields are drastically amplified, they are still bound by universal reality constants. The matrix is incapable of fully compressing supreme world anomalies, meaning it cannot contain or shackle catastrophic regional bosses."
	]
	quest.0594025A747665CF.quest_subtitle: "Expanding biological capture matrices to absorb massive extra-dimensional targets."
	quest.0594025A747665CF.title: "Pinnacle Containment: The Trinity Gem"
	quest.05FFFD19E6761FD9.quest_desc: ["Have a small chance to get it when enchanting."]
	quest.05FFFD19E6761FD9.quest_subtitle: "Chance of dropping when enchanting items"
	quest.068294A7C21DE550.quest_desc: ["&cTrack Kits&r are used to craft with &6rails&r to make special &6rails&r. \\n\\nThese &6rails&r will be helpful for everything &5Train&r wise like: stopping the &5Train&r, moving the &5Train&r, and emitting redstone."]
	quest.06D13E319C26C949.quest_desc: [
		"The Blood Mushroom Bog is home to giant Blood Mushrooms. "
		""
		"There is a deeply unsettling presence in the air here... so I think it is best to leave this entry short."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_blood.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.06D13E319C26C949.title: "Blood Mushroom Bog"
	quest.073BA8470EA37A00.quest_desc: [
		"Yet another endless expanse of water stretches into the gloom, though this sea bites back with a paralyzing, unnatural cold. "
		""
		"Its rigid waves whisper of forgotten depths, freezing the blood of any traveler daring enough to sail them."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_icey.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.073BA8470EA37A00.title: "Icy Sea"
	quest.08457BEED799E600.quest_desc: ["These new &7Carts&r are mostly for laying down &6Tracks&r.\\n\\nThe &7Track Layer&r places down &6Tracks&r while the &7Track Remover&r removes &6Tracks&r.\\n\\nThe &7Track Relayer&r replaces the &6Tracks&r with different ones and the &7Track UnderCutter&r replaces the blocks beneath the &6Tracks&r."]
	quest.08D9C809CF4062E8.quest_desc: [
		"The Underbean stands as the true cornerstone of subterranean survival, a versatile harvest that has kept many explorers from starvation. "
		""
		"Its firm texture allows it to be consumed raw directly from the vine for a quick burst of energy on the trail. "
		""
		"Alternatively, when subjected to the heat of a crackling campfire, they can be slow-roasted to bring out a rich, smoky flavor, or skewered upon a sharpened stick for a hearty, mobile meal. "
		""
		"In these harsh lands, it is the ultimate staple—there is virtually no limit to how it can sustain you."
	]
	quest.08FCBB3A1B289757.quest_desc: ["Dropped by The Wither."]
	quest.08FCBB3A1B289757.quest_subtitle: "Dropped by the Wither"
	quest.092BB595F75D5536.quest_desc: ["Welcome to &6&lForbidden \\& Arcanus&r! \\n\\nTo start this Mod we'll need to start Mining underground... deep underground. \\n\\nLike Y Level 1 and below. "]
	quest.092BB595F75D5536.title: "&6&lForbidden \\& Arcanus"
	quest.0A0A991BAC99092C.quest_desc: [
		"The Indigo Mushroom Bog is far more densely choked with life than its crimson counterpart, the Blood Mushroom Bog. "
		""
		"Naturally, it is home to thriving Indigo Mushrooms, but it also conceals twisted Mini Smogstem Trees and stagnant ponds of a glowing Virulent Mix. "
		""
		"I cannot help but wonder what corruptive power that mixture possesses..."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_indigo.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.0A0A991BAC99092C.title: "Indigo Mushroom Bog"
	quest.0A1D6E233C0ECC8E.quest_desc: [
		"The vicious predators known as &dNargoyles&r claim absolute dominion over the deep earth, manifesting as a persistent plague within the dark tunnels underground. "
		""
		"Possessing a resilient vitality equivalent to fifteen standard measures of health, these unrelenting horrors will lock onto your scent and pursue you to the ends of the cavern with a singular, bloodthirsty focus. "
		""
		"They offer absolutely no salvageable materials or precious drops upon their destruction. "
		""
		"They exist purely as a chaotic, lethal obstacle, explicitly designed to butcher any miner who dares to shatter the silence of the stone."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_nargoyle.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.0A1D6E233C0ECC8E.title: "&dNargoyle&r"
	quest.0A43FD0B5C76C1C5.quest_desc: [
		"&l&7RailCraft&r adds a Blast Furnace multiblock for us to transform Iron into Steel! \\n\\nTo build it you'll need 34 Blast Furnace Bricks. It'll be 3 blocks wide, 3 blocks long, and 4 blocks tall. The two blocks in the exact center need to be hollow. You'll know it's done when it forms all together and allows you to access its GUI. \\n\\nThere you can put Iron ,in any form, to get Steel and Granulated Sand."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_furnace.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.0A5AE5ADB477805C.quest_desc: [
		"While your entry-tier &eFoliot Crusher&r served as an adequate baseline for early operations, scaling your automated factory lines demands the absolute maximum optimization of your mineral logistics."
		""
		"Deploying the top-tier &9Marid Crusher&r introduces a massive breakthrough to your processing lines, multiplying every single raw ore fed into its matrix into an unprecedented six refined dusts. This ultimate level of resource generation completely eclipses all standard machinery and lower-tier spirits in the modpack."
		""
		"To shackle an entity of this extreme power and capture its high-output crushing metrics, you must layout and construct the complex geometric multi-block for &9Fatma's Incentivized Attraction&r."
	]
	quest.0A5AE5ADB477805C.quest_subtitle: "Maximizing factory throughput with a sextuple ore-multiplication circuit."
	quest.0A5AE5ADB477805C.title: "Pinnacle Refinement: The &9Marid Crusher&r"
	quest.0AE0E58BA5703400.quest_desc: ["Slay the Snow Queen found at the top of the Aurora Palace."]
	quest.0AE0E58BA5703400.title: "Slay a Snow Queen"
	quest.0B1DF8A040826D87.quest_desc: [
		"Now that you have &cRossinite&r, you can mix it with &aBenitoite&r to create &dInsanite&r ingots."
		""
		"&aBenitoite Ore&r can be found in the Nether."
	]
	quest.0B51F404F1E84C17.quest_desc: [
		"Step 3: Town Hall"
		""
		"The Town Hall block is what actually creates the colony. It also functions as the center of it. This is where you start using the build tool to place buildings. Using the build tool ensures you can see exactly where the building will be, which direction it will face, and if it is at the right Y level (some buildings need to be raised to the correct Y level)."
		""
		"Once the Town Hall block is placed, you will start receiving your initial 4 citizens."
		""
		"The protected area of your colony (once the Town Hall has been placed) will be a square 4 chunks in radius, measured from the chunk where you placed your Town Hall block the first time (with the default config). Therefore, plan carefully where you want to place your Town Hall. 64 blocks (4 chunks x 4 chunks) in every direction from that chunk will be your protected Town area including mountains, hills, lakes, oceans, caves, world generated structures, etc. from bedrock to sky limit."
		""
		"Hint: The most important tool you will need for the entire mod is the build tool (check our build tool page). Obtain one from the Supply Ship/Camp or craft another so you can place all the huts (including the Town Hall) in the perfect spot."
		""
		"Due to the protected area of each colony, you have to carefully scout your surrounding to make sure you are clear of any other colonies nearby preventing you from placing your Town Hall or limiting your colony area in that direction (in multiplayer, etc.). If there is another colony too close to your current position, you won’t be able to place a Town Hall."
		""
		"Location info of the next closest colony exists in the debug screen (displayed when you press F3). If there is a colony close to your current position, it will also show you the required distance away to place your Town Hall."
	]
	quest.0B51F404F1E84C17.title: "Town Hall"
	quest.0B9CBAC5D036021A.quest_subtitle: "Discover a new way of dealing ranged damage"
	quest.0BC2506F05B65F3C.quest_desc: ["Find a Quest Grove and give every colour of wool to the ram."]
	quest.0BF40B5B6ED8203F.quest_subtitle: "Craft yourself a new start with skyroot"
	quest.0BF40B5B6ED8203F.title: "New Wood!"
	quest.0C98503A2F20484D.quest_desc: [
		"Bordering the frozen wastes lie the Frosty Smogstem Forests, where the biting cold of the Frostfields collides with a suffocating canopy. "
		""
		"Here, the dead landscape is overrun by colossal Smogstem Trees, their frozen branches trapping the pale mist in a perpetual, freezing gloom."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_frostytrees.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.0C98503A2F20484D.title: "Frosty Smogstem Forest"
	quest.0D15A75331737FBB.quest_desc: [
		"Constructing the final geometric perimeter for &9Uphyxes' Inverted Tower&r grants your facility access to the pinnacle tier of &6Infusion Rituals&r. While this highly advanced configuration operates with highly specialized parameters and features a narrow catalog of recipes, its activation is strictly mandatory to unlock late-game logistical progression."
		""
		"The primary function of this heavy atmospheric matrix is the synthesis of Dragonyst Dust. This hyper-dense, extra-dimensional compound acts as your final core alchemical catalyst. Extracting this refined particle from the center of the infusion circle allows you to combine it with your existing chalk inventory to engineer your final sticks of Magenta Chalk modifiers."
	]
	quest.0D15A75331737FBB.quest_subtitle: "Harnessing maximum-tier atmospheric compression for final elemental transmutations."
	quest.0D15A75331737FBB.title: "Zenith Synthesis: &9Uphyxes' Inverted Tower&r"
	quest.0D56A15EC335C11A.quest_subtitle: "This ice has fused with stone itself, creating a new type of block with some unique uses"
	quest.0D56A15EC335C11A.title: "Compressed Ice"
	quest.0D91A6B36BD2F526.quest_desc: [
		"When wielding the formidable &7Cloggrum Battleaxe&r, a warrior commands an offensive weight only slightly inferior to the legendary density of diamond weaponry. "
		""
		"The crude, heavy craftsmanship anchors each swing firmly into the enemy, delivering immense kinetic shock to break through defensive stances. "
		""
		"However, this sheer mass demands a ruthless physical sacrifice. "
		""
		"The heavy, unyielding balance limits rapid recovery, locking the wielder into a precise combat rhythm and requiring a deliberate approach to every skirmish. "
		""
		"It is an instrument designed for the immovable executioner, not the swift duelist."
	]
	quest.0D91A6B36BD2F526.title: "Ultimate Weapon!"
	quest.0F00BBDF3618B3BA.quest_desc: [
		"While a standard viewport allows a logistics officer to survey an outpost's hoard, an efficient garrison demands the immediate synthesis of components without constantly shifting between a ledger and an anvil. "
		""
		"To streamline terminal operations, an engineer must construct the highly prioritized &3Crafting Grid&r. "
		""
		"This elite workstation maintains full administrative access to your digital storage vaults while seamlessly embedding an active matter-assembly matrix directly into the screen interface. "
		""
		"It stands as an absolute triumph of industrial design; indeed, within advanced colonies, the primitive, non-crafting &3Grid&r models have been completely abandoned by technicians who refuse to tolerate unnecessary steps during frontline manufacturing routines."
	]
	quest.0F00BBDF3618B3BA.quest_subtitle: "Section XX: Integrated Matter Assembly Interfaces"
	quest.0F00BBDF3618B3BA.title: "Advanced Workstation: Workbench Display Terminals"
	quest.0FA77C28A57E06F1.quest_desc: [
		"The Veiled Mushrooms are a highly specialized species, bound entirely to the damp microclimate of their native bogs. "
		""
		"They are easily recognized by their somber, mud-brown caps, but their true wonder is a mechanical reflex triggered by the atmosphere. "
		""
		"Should the earth fall away beneath them, leaving nothing but empty air, the exposed gills immediately begin spinning delicate, cascading structures known as Mushroom Veils. "
		""
		"It is a striking defense mechanism, clothing the empty space below in a shifting shroud of living mesh."
	]
	quest.0FFF3856AE0806F6.quest_subtitle: "Obtain a weapon fitting for a heavenly challenger from the bronze dungeon"
	quest.0FFF3856AE0806F6.title: "Better than a sword!"
	quest.100CF061D413A567.quest_subtitle: "Grab yourself some sunscreen, live a healthy lifestyle!"
	quest.100CF061D413A567.title: "Prepare adequately"
	quest.103F99D9C4385248.quest_desc: [
		"With your Foliot Crusher successfully bound to the material plane, you can now &mexploit&r utilize its brute processing strength to pulverize high-density compounds."
		""
		"Your next logistical milestone requires feeding the spirit raw quantities of &eEnd Stone&r, &9Obsidian&r, and &7Calcite&r. The entity will rapidly grind these dense materials into specialized, hyper-purified dusts—vital alchemical components absolutely required to forge your next tier of ritual chalks."
	]
	quest.103F99D9C4385248.title: "&aRefining the Medium"
	quest.104EBBC08B4733F5.quest_desc: ["The &dSimulation Chamber&r is the main machine within HNN.\\n\\nWhen given power, it will run simulations based on the &bData Model&r that is placed inside. The power required also depends on the Data Model placed inside, and can be seen within the Model's tooltip. \\n\\nThe machine also requires at least one &9Prediction Matrix&r to run a simulation.\\n\\nThe result of the simulation will be output onto the Matrix. Simulations will always produce some kind of &eGeneralized Prediction&r, which can be used in various crafting recipes. They also vary depending on the origin of the mob in the Data Model.\\n\\nIf the simulation succeeds, you will receive a &dMob Prediction&r based off of the model. The higher the tier of the Data Model used, the higher the success rate is for a simulation."]
	quest.104EBBC08B4733F5.title: "&aSimulating Deaths"
	quest.1054168AFD8520D4.quest_desc: [
		"The monumental titan known as the &aForgotten Guardian&r stands as a colossal golem forged entirely from pure, compressed &aBlock of Forgotten Ingots&r. "
		""
		"Animated by a relentless, primeval malice, this monolithic sentinel will immediately lock onto any trespassing traveler, executing a brutal, unyielding campaign to crush them into dust. "
		""
		"It possesses a staggering, near-impenetrable vitality equivalent to one hundred and sixty standard measures of health, rendering normal blades practically useless against its frame. "
		""
		"Should an exceptionally legendary warrior somehow shatter its defenses and bring about its ruin, its exploding core will surrender a precious scattering of highly coveted &aForgotten Nuggets&r."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_guardian.png width:100 height:200 align:center}"
	]
	quest.1054168AFD8520D4.title: "&aForgotten Guardian&r"
	quest.10B6FDA1362E3C52.quest_desc: [
		"This advanced tool serves as the ultimate functional upgrade to the Rainbow Chalk, engineered specifically for facility designers who prefer a pristine, unified laboratory environment over rapid, flashing color loops."
		""
		"The apparatus retains the exact same master-tier utility as its rainbow counterpart, but completely dampens the chaotic visual shifts. When drawn onto the floor, every single runic glyph manifests as a clean, uniform white engraving—allowing you to maintain a highly polished, cohesive aesthetic across your entire ritual floor without sacrificing an ounce of performance."
		""
		"Beyond the cosmetic refinement, this tool introduces a critical structural upgrade. While the previous rainbow model was strictly limited to colored modifiers, this advanced matrix successfully incorporates monochrome compression logic. This means a single tool now seamlessly mimics both color parameters and every tier of Foundation Chalk (from White up to midnight Black Chalk)—effectively consolidating your entire occult scribing inventory into one singular, infinite-durability instrument."
	]
	quest.10B6FDA1362E3C52.quest_subtitle: "Consolidating the full structural spectrum into a clean, unyielding visual layout."
	quest.10B6FDA1362E3C52.title: "Monochromatic Synthesis: Void Chalk"
	quest.10E8BC20D406D9FB.quest_subtitle: "Makes various Nether Materials"
	quest.1187F9D4F4E0D254.quest_desc: [
		"The &3Wrench&r stands as an indispensable, dual-purpose implement forged explicitly for the physical upkeep and structural calibration of a digital network. "
		""
		"This specialized hardware tool bypasses standard masonry demolition methods, offering an engineer two critical mechanical functions on the maintenance line. "
		""
		"It can immediately re-align and rotate massive network blocks along their axial planes without breaking their internal wiring, and it can seamlessly dislodge and snap off protective covers without shattering the delicate facades beneath. "
		""
		"Activating these precise structural overrides mandates a strict manipulation protocol: the technician must drop into a low, concentrated sneak posture before executing a firm right-click strike upon the targeted block mechanism."
	]
	quest.1187F9D4F4E0D254.quest_subtitle: "Section III: The Multi-Functional Network Implement"
	quest.1187F9D4F4E0D254.title: "Hardware Tool: Logistical Calibration"
	quest.1190BB433EFA3945.quest_desc: [
		"The mechanical armament designated as the Slingshot stands as a remarkably versatile, highly unconventional weapon engineered within the boundaries of the &2&lUndergarden&r. "
		""
		"Utilizing a specialized tensile band, it is designed to chamber and launch four distinct variants of ammunition, each introducing a unique tactical payload upon the battlefield."
		""
		"Scintling Goo: Projectiles composed of this viscous fluid burst upon impact, instantly inflicting the restrictive Gooey Effect to trap fast-moving targets in a suffocating residue."
		""
		"Depthrock Pebbles: Deployed as the standard, high-velocity kinetic munition for reliable blunt-force trauma."
		""
		"Rotten Blisterberries: Volatile payloads that react violently upon physical contact, triggering a localized explosion to tear through tightly packed enemy formations."
		""
		"&eGronglets&r: This unique vegetative ammo inflicts zero structural damage upon a target, serving strictly as a psychological deterrent by projecting a sudden, disorienting burst of noise where they land.\""
	]
	quest.119242549BD21764.quest_desc: [
		"The massive creatures known as &eBrutes&r roam across a select few biomes, maintaining a tense, neutral stance toward outsiders. "
		""
		"They possess a fierce, pack-minded loyalty that mirrors the defensive packs of wild wolves or the dreaded zombified piglins of the nether expanses. "
		""
		"To strike a single beast is to invite immediate doom; a lone blow will echo across the territory, driving every nearby pack member into a synchronized, relentless frenzy against the aggressor. "
		""
		"Should you successfully bring down one of these titans, their remains may yield their massive tusks—a dense, calcified material that carvers have found to be a perfect, structural replacement for traditional bone."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_brute.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.119242549BD21764.title: "&eBrutes&r"
	quest.1278DBA393B22F10.quest_desc: ["Found in large ice caves."]
	quest.1278DBA393B22F10.title: "Slay an Alpha Yeti"
	quest.12A43F82FC67A289.quest_desc: [
		"To secure the physical storage of digitized items across the main network bus line, an engineer must construct specialized digital media disks. "
		""
		"These fragile storage cells cannot simply be left loose upon an anvil; they must be securely slid into a centralized &9Disk Drive&r assembly that is wired directly into your active network grid. "
		""
		"This heavy hardware docking bay features exactly eight structural slots engineered to accept individual Storage Disks. "
		""
		"By filling these bays to maximum capacity, a logistics officer can stack massive storage thresholds into a single, compact block location, providing an expansive, stable data foundation for a colony's expanding empire."
	]
	quest.12A43F82FC67A289.quest_subtitle: "Section XV: Mass Data Drive Configurations"
	quest.12A43F82FC67A289.title: "Memory Bay: Digital Storage Array's"
	quest.12E5DD67806388F3.quest_subtitle: "Combine with Glowstone for the ultimate builder experience"
	quest.12E5DD67806388F3.title: "Glorious Brick"
	quest.130577AD1A1A8222.quest_desc: [
		"While a full set of &7Cloggrum&r Armor offers a defensive threshold slightly inferior to the refined iron plating of the surface world, its staggering abundance across the realm makes it an indispensable asset for common survival. "
		""
		"It is a material so easily pulled from the earth that it presents virtually no burden to replace. "
		""
		"Furthermore, armorers have introduced a crucial adaptation to the footwear; the heavy, dense composition of the &7Cloggrum&r Boots creates a specialized weight distribution, allowing travelers to march through the sticky, restrictive fields of Scintling Goo without losing their footing."
	]
	quest.130577AD1A1A8222.title: "&7Cloggrum&r Armor"
	quest.13B658487B62A140.quest_subtitle: "Home to the Sun Spirit"
	quest.13B658487B62A140.title: "Find The Golden Island"
	quest.141681FE9E524FB0.quest_desc: [
		"The skeletal sentinels known as &7Forgottens&r endure as the tireless warriors bound eternally to the crumbling halls of the Catacomb Structure. "
		""
		"Clad in the rusted plating of Ancient Armor and clutching heavy Cloggrum Tools, these hollow soldiers carry weapons and defenses that can be completely plundered from their shattered frames upon their definitive fall. "
		""
		"Mysteriously, a flicker of their ancient allegiance remains locked within their bones; they harbor an absolute, unyielding hatred for the blighted &cRot Mobs&r, aggressively tracking and executing them whenever their paths cross within the dark corridors."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_forgotten.png width:100 height:200 align:center}"
	]
	quest.141681FE9E524FB0.title: "Forgotten"
	quest.145414B77583E1AA.quest_subtitle: "Open 100 Containers"
	quest.14B3542ECB59869C.quest_desc: ["The &5Loot Fabricator&r is the machine that gets you that sweet, sweet loot from Mob Predictions.\\n\\nWhen given power and a successful Mob Prediction, you will be able to choose which item you'd like to get from that mob's Data Model. The machine will remember your choice, so it can be automated.\\n\\nExamples of Mob Predictions:\\n\\n- &dEnder Dragons&r for &dDragon Eggs\\n - &2Zombies&r for Iron\\n - &0Withers&r for &5Nether Stars"]
	quest.14B3542ECB59869C.title: "Creating &dLoot"
	quest.14E5349DD740D026.quest_desc: [
		"To insert fuel into the reactor, you'll need to pick one of the sides that has a &9Reactor Solid Access Port&r and pump in &eUranium&r from an inventory."
		""
		"The easiest way to do this is to use something like a &aStorage Drawer&r or even just a &aChest&r with an &9Item Pipe&r connected at the top, like the image shown below.\\n"
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/import.png width:150 height:150 align:center}"
	]
	quest.14E5349DD740D026.title: "Passive Reactor Fueling"
	quest.14E93FEC6AE1ABA9.quest_subtitle: "These non craftable tools of glory seem to greatly increase your reach"
	quest.14E93FEC6AE1ABA9.title: " Holy Arms"
	quest.1565DEE3F59CEDD4.title: "Visit the Twilight Forest"
	quest.15A8F04BC10E619E.quest_desc: [
		"While most flora in these lands isolates itself to specific realms, the Dense Forest defies the natural order. "
		""
		"It is as if an ancient force gathered the saplings of the world and bound them together within this single, tangled canopy."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_dense.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.15A8F04BC10E619E.title: "Dense Forest"
	quest.15ECBC8E174FA39B.quest_desc: [
		"To break the physical shackles of stationary terminals and achieve total logistical mobility across the frontier, a vanguard commander must forge the &9Wireless Grid&r."
		""
		"This highly sophisticated, hand-held transceiver allows an operative to securely access their central network storage wirelessly from anywhere within the broadcasting zone."
		""
		"By tapping directly into the atmospheric signal projected by your facility's transmitters, this mobile viewport exposes the entire digitized database."
		""
		"It enables a scout to instantly survey imperial stockpiles, withdraw heavy munitions, or deposit rare minerals directly into the virtual vaults without ever setting foot back inside the fortress walls."
	]
	quest.15ECBC8E174FA39B.quest_subtitle: "Section XXVII: The Wireless Grid Terminal"
	quest.15ECBC8E174FA39B.title: "Remote Viewport: Mobile Data Access"
	quest.161865F4B886E5B7.quest_desc: ["Not everything here seems friendly to strangers, angry clouds, poison spewing plants and chickens combined with a mysterious darkness give off the feeling of a hostile paradise, maybe we aren't as welcome here as we initially thought?"]
	quest.161865F4B886E5B7.quest_subtitle: "Every poison has its antidote"
	quest.161865F4B886E5B7.title: "Perfect Paradise?"
	quest.1698565EBB68DC85.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Wye Track&r is the second track made by using a Spike Maul. It directs two &6Tracks&r into one. If you have one &6Track&r intersected by another the &6Wye&r will move &7Carts&r on the first &6Track&r into the intersecting one."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_wye.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.16A04B2FC3F0D902.quest_desc: [
		"The archaic implements known as &7Cloggrum&r Tools serve as a reliable, rugged alternative to standard iron hardware, though their textured surfaces bear a striking resemblance to compressed, dried mud rather than refined ore. "
		""
		"Do not let their primitive, earth-stained appearance deceive you; they possess a surprising resilience and utilitarian efficiency. "
		""
		"Furthermore, smiths have discovered that the dense composition of this material grants the &7Cloggrum&r Sword an unmatched weight, allowing it to deliver significantly more devastating damage upon a target than a blade forged from common iron."
	]
	quest.16A04B2FC3F0D902.title: "&7Cloggrum&r Tools"
	quest.170118E3C3C072E5.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Junction&r is the last &6Track&r made by the Spike Maul. It acts as a normal intersection for &6Tracks. &7Carts&r keep going the same way as before but now &6Tracks&r can intersect. What happens if 2 &7Carts&r hit each other on it? THEY EXPLODE!!! I'm kidding but &eElectric Locomotives&r will though."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_junction.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.17452A76067CC6C0.quest_desc: ["Found in Mineshafts."]
	quest.17452A76067CC6C0.quest_subtitle: "Found in Mineshaft chests"
	quest.175D943160C10646.quest_desc: [
		"&l&7RailCraft&r uses many machines for different things but mostly resource creation."
		""
		"All of them start with Iron Ingots!"
	]
	quest.17A8939CE5BF7ED8.quest_desc: [
		"Manufacturing your final sticks of Magenta Chalk requires you to establish a synchronized cross-tier production chain. While initializing &9Uphyxes' Inverted Tower&r provides the core synthesis path needed to extract Dragonyst Dust, your facility cannot process this raw particle into a usable runic medium using basic machinery."
		""
		"To finalize the compound, you must simultaneously deploy your top-tier &9Marid Crusher&r network. This spirit-crushing circuit is uniquely capable of pulverizing the dense, advanced materials required to bind and stabilize the dust. Routing the output of both maximum-tier operations into a single crafting grid is mandatory to forge your final colored modifiers."
	]
	quest.17A8939CE5BF7ED8.quest_subtitle: "Synchronizing maximum-tier infusion outputs with advanced mineral crushing loops."
	quest.17A8939CE5BF7ED8.title: "Cross-Tier Integration: Magenta Chalk"
	quest.17C2C8F64B4AE6EE.quest_desc: [
		"The sluggish beasts known as &2Dwellers&r serve as the primary livestock within the &2&lUndergarden&r, mirroring the domestic role that cattle hold in the surface world. "
		""
		"They are entirely passive creatures, wandering the dim landscapes with a heavy, harmless gait. "
		""
		"Should they be slaughtered for survival, their carcasses yield a coarse leather suitable for basic crafting, alongside a dense supply of raw Dweller Meat. "
		""
		"Mysteriously, these mammals possess no harvestable milk—a biological mercy that seasoned explorers are deeply grateful for, given the unsettling fluids that course through their subterranean bodies."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_dweller.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.17C2C8F64B4AE6EE.title: "&2Dweller&r"
	quest.17F7964611D893BE.quest_desc: ["The Fluid Loader will be helpful to keeping your &3Steam Locomotives&r up and running. It has to be placed a few blocks above the &6Tracks&r and it will deploy fluids into either the &5Locomotive&r or &7Carts&r."]
	quest.1808E988F815E641.quest_subtitle: "Highly resistant clouds"
	quest.1808E988F815E641.title: "New Building Materials!"
	quest.184F98BE0F6710E2.quest_desc: ["These 2 &cTrack Kits&r are for using &7Carts&r and Redstone.\\n\\nThe &cActivator Kit&r will activate whatever &7Cart&r goes over it. \\nThe &cDetector Kit&r will activate a redstone signal whenever a &7Cart&r passes over it. \\n\\nBoth are similar to their &2Vanilla&r counters for regular &6tracks&r."]
	quest.186731580B14F9D2.quest_desc: [
		"To interact with our Turbine, we'll need several &6Ports&r."
		""
		"The &9Fluid Port&r is used to insert vapors like &bSteam&r, or extract exhaust, like &9water&r. "
		""
		"Because of this, you'll need two for your Turbine."
		""
		"The &cPower Tap&r extracts power, and is required to complete the multiblock."
	]
	quest.186731580B14F9D2.title: "Port O' Turbine"
	quest.19047AF0EDED198B.quest_desc: [
		"No ritual matrix is complete without a proper &cSacrifice&r to appease the entities waiting on the other side."
		""
		"Fortunately, lower-tier spirits generally only demand physical catalysts rather than living blood, meaning your livestock is safe for now. You will utilize &aSacrificial Bowls&r to hold these necessary material offerings. "
		""
		"These pedestals can be placed freely around your ritual area, provided they do not obstruct or sit directly on top of the chalk glyphs forming the outer circles."
		""
		"While your current ceremonies only demand a cluster of four bowls, advanced rituals deeper in the tech tree will require upwards of ten peripheral bowls to feed the matrix."
		""
		"The central anchor of your setup is the &6Golden Ritual Bowl&r. Positioned directly in the geographic center of your pentacle, this block is used to initiate the ritual, and is almost always the vessel where your prepared Book of Binding must be placed to spark the summoning process."
	]
	quest.19047AF0EDED198B.title: "&4Blood&r and &6Offerings"
	quest.19689F3D7477D89D.quest_desc: ["Found in Pillager Outposts,"]
	quest.19689F3D7477D89D.quest_subtitle: "Found in Pillager Outpost chests"
	quest.1984ECEC68F48221.quest_desc: [
		"While transmuting resources via &dSpiritfire&r is highly efficient, you can also deploy specialized &9Divination Rods&r to survey and extract raw, hidden deposits directly from the environment."
		""
		"efore scanning, the instrument must be properly calibrated. To attune the rod, simply right-click an overworld block that corresponds to the target material you wish to hunt. For instance, right-clicking standard &aAndesite&r will program the rod's frequencies to detect underground veins of hidden &8Otherstone&r."
		""
		"Once attuned, holding right-click with the rod will project a continuous stream of resonance particles, pointing directly toward the geometric coordinates of the nearest matching node."
		""
		"Note that while the rod handles the physical location tracking, it does not bypass the planar barrier. You must still be under the active status effects of the &3Third Eye&r to pierce the illusion and successfully harvest the revealed blocks."
	]
	quest.1984ECEC68F48221.quest_subtitle: "Hunting for Materials"
	quest.1984ECEC68F48221.title: "Holy Tools"
	quest.19D85E1B63ADFF34.quest_desc: [
		"Step 1: Supply Camp/Supply Ship"
		""
		"Once you have chosen a location for your colony, you must place a Supply Ship or Supply Camp. You can only place one of these per world. The Supply Camp/Ship gives you the Town Hall block you need to officially start your colony. They also have some other supplies you may need during the building of your colony. Once you have the Town Hall block and the build tool, the remaining camp/ship is just decoration. You can leave it or tear it down."
		""
		"To place the Supply Camp, you need to have a large enough flat, clear piece of land (at least 16x17 blocks)."
		""
		"When you place the Supply Camp, it will spawn a chest that will contain the Town Hall block and the build tool. Once the Supply Camp is placed, you can’t place another in the world."
		""
		"Place the Supply Camp by right-clicking the item directly on the water/ground – if you have a build tool already, don’t use it for this (you’re expected to get the tool from the camp rather than already having one)."
		""
		"Hint: If you’re not able to place the Supply Camp, try it block by block: one to the right, left, closer or further from the area you cleared. The area cannot contain any holes or have any flowers, grass, ferns, seaweed, coral etc."
	]
	quest.1A67AF47E8282424.quest_subtitle: "Find an egg dropped rarely by a naturally spawned moa, or just steal one from a chest"
	quest.1A67AF47E8282424.title: "Moas are BACK!"
	quest.1B0EDBFE8ED76110.quest_subtitle: "Tools made with this stone have a chance to drop amrbosium shards when used"
	quest.1B0EDBFE8ED76110.title: "Holier Stone"
	quest.1BAE1519E44E40CE.quest_desc: [
		"Take the Ancient Sea and drain it of all its kelp, leaving it entirely devoid of &bGwibs&r and &bGwiblings&r. \\n\\nWhat remains is the Dead Sea."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_dead.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.1BAE1519E44E40CE.title: "Dead Sea"
	quest.1C232674CD04024D.quest_desc: [
		"The &2&lUndergarden&r stands as a sprawling subterranean expanse, a realm defined by its starkly diverse and grotesque biomes. "
		""
		"Within its shadowed folds, an overwhelming abundance of alien vegetation thrives alongside a host of unpredictable entities—some deceptively docile, others overtly hostile. "
		""
		"Rich veins of untamed ores and forgotten relics lie buried deep beneath the soil, waiting to be claimed. "
		""
		"Steel your resolve, traveler, for this land demands blood, and a desperate struggle for survival awaits any who cross the threshold."
	]
	quest.1C232674CD04024D.quest_subtitle: "Take Us to the Threshold!"
	quest.1C232674CD04024D.title: "Welcome to the &2&lUndergarden&r!"
	quest.1C9032F0B333E605.quest_subtitle: "Gear made out of this gem seems to be on the same level as iron, however they  bear an innate effect of increasing efficiency the closer they are to being broken"
	quest.1C9032F0B333E605.title: "New Iron?"
	quest.1CF790252F0F1A77.quest_subtitle: "You've obtained temporal control over the aether, congrats!"
	quest.1CF790252F0F1A77.title: "The Final Block"
	quest.1E13D7CE5A9EFF74.quest_desc: [
		"The Frostfields stretch out as one of the most frigid, unforgiving biomes within the &2&lUndergarden&r. "
		""
		"Towering icicles pierce the gloom, overlooking vast drifts of Powdered Snow and brittle, Frozen Deepturf. "
		""
		"Deep beneath the surface, the standard Depthrock gives way to Shiverstone—a deceitful material that looks like stone, but behaves like slick, treacherous ice to anyone foolish enough to step on it."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_frosty.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.1E13D7CE5A9EFF74.title: "Frostfields"
	quest.1E81B903137BB62A.quest_desc: [
		"Standard implements of war will rapidly fail when matched against the horrific predators stalking the &2&lUndergarden&r. "
		""
		"To withstand their onslaught, an artisan can forge the sturdy &7Cloggrum Shield&r, a bulwark that matches the reliable defensive capabilities of common surface shields. "
		""
		"However, acquiring true offensive supremacy requires unearthing a relic of the past: the devastating &7Battleaxe&r. "
		""
		"This heavy weapon cannot be crafted by mortal hands; it must be wrenched as a rare, hard-won trophy from the shattered remains of the tomb-dwelling &7Forgottens&r."
	]
	quest.1E81B903137BB62A.title: "&7Cloggrum&r Weapons"
	quest.1E8AEFFA2E43CAFC.quest_desc: [
		"Your structural offerings are not strictly limited to basic stone; you can also manufacture &cCopper Sacrificial Bowls&r and &cSilver Sacrificial Bowls&r to line your pentacle perimeters."
		""
		"While these metallic tiers are entirely cosmetic and introduce zero functional modifications to your ritual speed or material efficiency, they provide a significantly more polished, high-tier architectural aesthetic for an established automation laboratory."
	]
	quest.1E8AEFFA2E43CAFC.title: "Aesthetic Realignment"
	quest.1F70366D737E9FBC.quest_desc: [
		"You will find a cross-mod bridge from Ars Nouveau resting within this tech branch, made possible by the integration features of Ars Occultas. This bridge allows your summoned entities—such as the &aFoliot Crusher&r—to be securely housed inside these containment jars."
		""
		"Once an entity is sealed inside, you can pipe raw materials directly into the jar's input matrix. The resident spirit will instantly process the items and automatically export the finished products into any directly adjacent inventory."
		""
		"When configuring your logistics lines, note that utilizing the bottom face of the jar provides the most consistent and reliable automation export connection. Be aware that if no valid storage container or pipe interface is detected on an adjacent face, the spirit will simply drop the processed items directly into the world as loose entities."
	]
	quest.1F70366D737E9FBC.quest_subtitle: "Imprisoning lesser entities to serve as infinite, power-free factory workers."
	quest.1F70366D737E9FBC.title: "Arcane Isolation: &aContainment Jars&r"
	quest.1FCF946B7BE3C0BD.quest_desc: [
		"Implements forged from the volatile ore known as &cUtherium&r match the flawless cutting precision and structural durability of standard diamond hardware. "
		""
		"However, these specialized armaments harbor a profound biological paradox within their glowing edges. "
		""
		"When drawn against the corrupted forces of the blight, the weapons react with immense kinetic fury, proving significantly more effective at purging &cRot Mobs&r than any diamond blade could achieve. "
		""
		"It is a brilliant, cyclic law of metallurgy: the very essence harvested from the remains of the infected is weaponized directly against them, striking down the monsters with the refined power of their own toxic lineage."
	]
	quest.1FCF946B7BE3C0BD.title: "&cUtheric&r Tools"
	quest.2009CB12D69BCED8.quest_subtitle: "Meet the majestic ruler of the clouds, the untouchable aerwhale!"
	quest.202C506FA06B4E39.quest_desc: ["Buy it from a master cleric."]
	quest.204D53D25ECC3882.quest_subtitle: "This ice powered machine can automate the freezing process and even adds some new items"
	quest.204D53D25ECC3882.title: "Fridge?"
	quest.210EF23262133E20.quest_subtitle: "Find the fuel from the heavens"
	quest.210EF23262133E20.title: "Holy Coal!"
	quest.21693C4DE6531D73.quest_desc: [
		"The Crusher is just as the name suggests. It can crush blocks to get the crafting materials, like bricks from a brick staircase, or dusts from ingots. \\n\\nIt needs power to work though! \\n\\nTo build one it's 3x2x2 of Crusher blocks."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_crusher.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.216FAD99B6E85C69.quest_desc: ["Fishing loot."]
	quest.21FF14E8B61F515F.quest_desc: [
		"Reaching the pinnacle of geometric design allows you to permanently solve the inventory clutter of your scribing toolkit. Activating the ultimate matrix of &dRonaza's Contact&r allows you to combine your entire chemical arsenal into a singular, mastery-tier instrument: the Rainbow Chalk."
		""
		"Once forged from the center of the circle, this tool completely eliminates the need to haul sixteen separate colored chalk sticks across your base. When drawn into the world, the chalk creates a fluctuating, color-changing rune that dynamically morphs its frequency to satisfy the requirements of any colored glyph modifier within a multi-block layout. Furthermore, this advanced apparatus possesses infinite durability, removing all future tool restoration or material re-smelting cycles from your automation routine."
		""
		"Note that the rainbow matrix is strictly tuned to handle color parameters. It cannot mirror the dense material foundations required by monochrome paths (White, Light Gray, Gray, and Black Chalk). To achieve complete multi-block consolidation for your foundational lines, you must advance a step further and manufacture its sister component, the Void Chalk, to handle your base structural geometry."
	]
	quest.21FF14E8B61F515F.quest_subtitle: "Consolidating the colored runic spectrum into a single, infinite modifier tool."
	quest.21FF14E8B61F515F.title: "The Ultimate Medium: Rainbow Chalk"
	quest.22739522F0D33D7B.quest_desc: [
		"The Gloomgourd grows and spreads across the damp soil in a manner mirroring the common pumpkins of the surface world, sending out creeping vines that claim the earth. "
		""
		"Cultivators have found that its flesh can be safely hollowed out and baked into a rich, dark pie, or carved with leering faces and illuminated from within to create protective jack-o'-lanterns. "
		""
		"Yet, beneath its thick rind lies a volatile anatomy entirely alien to regular crops; when mixed with the correct catalysts, the compressed gases within the gourd react violently, allowing it to be repurposed into a devastating explosive."
	]
	quest.22F80D267321BFC5.quest_desc: [
		"As an industrial facility expands, manual tracking of scattered assembly nodes becomes an engineered logistical hazard."
		""
		"To establish absolute command over an empire's manufacturing layer, a technician must implement the &3Autocrafter Manager&r. "
		""
		"This advanced administrative terminal acts as a unified data gateway, allowing an operative to interface with, access, and reprogram every individual &3Autocrafter&r connected to the network from a single, centralized block location."
		""
		"However, experienced quartermasters issue a stern warning against attempting to meticulously organize and catalog every single automated schematic within this sprawling interface; "
		""
		"&ofor your own mental clarity and the safety of the base's computational mainframe, it is best to let the machines handle the data streams organically rather than forcing a strict order upon a chaotic matrix.&r"
	]
	quest.22F80D267321BFC5.quest_subtitle: "Section XXIV: Macro-Management of the Manufacturing Layer"
	quest.22F80D267321BFC5.title: "Grid Overseer: Archive Centralization Terminals"
	quest.23DB36F62D07026B.quest_desc: [
		"Constructing the complex geometric matrix for &dOsorin's Unbound Calling&r marks your entry into the second operational tier of &dDemon-less rituals&r. Because the foundational tier of this discipline focuses strictly on niche auxiliary operations—such as resurrecting fallen Familiars or cleansing hostile Vexes into friendly Allays—you can completely bypass it to focus your logistical resources here."
		""
		"This advanced, autonomous ritual circuit serves as a critical alternative manufacturing forge. By drawing upon raw energy directly from your chalk geometry rather than a bound entity, the matrix allows you to cleanly synthesize an immense array of exotic blocks, rare items, and dense materials that are otherwise locked behind complex inter-dimensional exploration loops or highly gated crafting recipes."
	]
	quest.23DB36F62D07026B.quest_subtitle: "Bypassing production bottlenecks through advanced demon-less transmutations."
	quest.23DB36F62D07026B.title: "Material Synthesis: &dOsorin's Unbound Calling&r"
	quest.23F691FC053F2319.quest_desc: [
		"When an imperial outpost expands to a scale that demands the complete migration of archived materials between independent mainframe systems, manual sorting through terminals becomes entirely obsolete."
		""
		"To execute a direct, low-level data extraction, an engineer must install the Disk Interface."
		""
		"This highly specialized computational manifold acts as a physical bridge between isolated digital sectors, allowing a technician to seamlessly extract thousands of digitized items and pressurized alchemical fluids directly from one storage disk and inject them straight into the media cells of a completely separate grid network."
		""
		"It stands as the definitive instrument for merging the logistical databases of conquered outposts or transitioning a colony's legacy vaults into a newly constructed master fortress."
	]
	quest.23F691FC053F2319.quest_subtitle: "Section XVI: Direct Media Inter-Data Transfer"
	quest.23F691FC053F2319.title: "Netowrk Amalgamation: Intra-Disk Terminal Bridges"
	quest.247AD8A7F03FC0B1.quest_subtitle: "Salvage those magnificent pillars to incorporate them in your next build!"
	quest.247AD8A7F03FC0B1.title: "Pillars"
	quest.249E5C6893387E15.quest_desc: ["These &cTracks&r are made for stopping the &5Locomotives&r and &7Carts&r. \\n\\nThe &cLocking Kit&r stops &7Carts&r and only starts them when given a redstone pulse. \\nThe &cBuffer Kit&r is for the end of your &6tracks&r, will stop them and not start. \\nThe &cGated Kit&r just deploys a Fence Gate connected with the &6track&r."]
	quest.24D38DA8E86DD897.quest_desc: [
		"The absolute lowest tier of the spreading corruption, this miserable creature crawls as the smallest and most fragile vector among the &cRot Mobs&r. "
		""
		"It possesses a frail, decaying vitality equivalent to a mere ten standard measures of health, making it an easy target for an alert traveler. "
		""
		"Driven by the primal, localized hatred inherent to all infected &cRot Mobs&r, it will mindlessly throw itself against the proud &2Stoneborns&r and the ancient &7Forgottens&r in a desperate attempt to spread its blight. "
		""
		"Upon its swift eradication, its dissolving tissue yields a small scattering of valuable &cUtheric Shards&r."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_rotling.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.24D38DA8E86DD897.title: "&cRotling&r"
	quest.253657BE5D9D9162.quest_desc: [
		"Before a colony commands the advanced processing units required to forge digital storage disks, a master architect must bridge the gap between archaic architecture and the digital grid. "
		""
		"This critical logistical transition is achieved via the External Storage cable interface—universally recognized as one of the most vital instruments an engineer can fabricate."
		""
		"When affixed to a legacy container, this specialized terminal link forces the network to map the physical space within."
		""
		"It translates raw, tangible inventories into a searchable data format, granting immediate read-and-write access directly through the central terminal Grid."
		""
		"The computational spectrum of this interface is remarkably broad, binding seamlessly to common wooden crates, reinforced barrels, localized storage drawers, and centralized drawer controller arrays."
		""
		"For defensive outposts choked with disorganized chests and lacking the resources for digital drives, this mechanism represents the definitive strategy to unify an empire's scattered assets under a single, cohesive command network."
	]
	quest.253657BE5D9D9162.quest_subtitle: "Section VI: Legacy Storage Amalgamation"
	quest.253657BE5D9D9162.title: "Buffer Interface: Data Integration Matrices"
	quest.2559201BCF5D497C.quest_subtitle: "Makes various Overworld Materials"
	quest.25D4406CB86C8CBB.quest_desc: [
		"Now that we are collecting some &9waste&r from our reactor, part of the progression requires you to \"Fluidize\" some of the ingots you get. "
		""
		"You know what that means?\\n\\nWe need to make a &aFluidizer&r! "
		""
		"The main component is the &aFluidizer Controller&r. Once built, you can right-click on this to open up the interface. "
		""
		"Here, you can turn it on or off, see what's inside, and the current power level."
	]
	quest.2615A9F7168A46CD.quest_subtitle: "Craft and sacrifice a piece of each of these new equipments to unlock further guidance"
	quest.2615A9F7168A46CD.title: "A whole new Inventory?"
	quest.265E6BBDB288E97A.quest_subtitle: "Open 25 containers"
	quest.26ACAAF08905AF85.quest_desc: [
		"Utilizing the structural alignment of &aIhagan's Enthrallment&r, you can execute a low-tier flying organism—such as an Allay, Bat, Bee, or Parrot—to anchor an otherworldly spirit to the physical plane. This sacrificial reaction forces the entity to manifest in the world as a highly hostile &6Possessed Bee&r."
		""
		"Upon terminating this corrupted entity, the matrix will collapse and yield Cursed Honey. This volatile byproduct cannot be consumed normally, serving instead as the core chemical ingredient strictly required to refine and manufacture your next tier of Orange Chalk."
	]
	quest.26ACAAF08905AF85.quest_subtitle: "Extracting localized biological drops for mid-tier chalk modifiers."
	quest.26ACAAF08905AF85.title: "Alchemical Metamorphosis: &aIhagan's Enthrallment&r"
	quest.26FDEE21CE8BBD6C.quest_desc: [
		"The denizens of the Otherworld demand a proper atmosphere, and almost every ritual requires the soft glow of candlelight to anchor the entities to our realm.To harvest the raw materials, craft a &aButcher Knife&r and slay livestock—such as pigs, cows, sheep, horses, or wandering trader llamas—to extract their &aTallow&r for candle crafting. "
		""
		"Alternatively, standard vanilla candles can serve as an acceptable substitute if you prefer to bypass the slaughter. &mJust don't ask what the wandering trader thinks about your resource gathering.&r"
		""
		"In addition to lighting, the ambient energy must be focused. "
		""
		"&9Spirit Attuned Crystals&r act as vital focal points for several upcoming advanced rituals, making it wise to secure a steady supply of them immediately."
	]
	quest.26FDEE21CE8BBD6C.title: "Preparing for a Ritual: &aCandles"
	quest.2742EF745632141A.quest_subtitle: "Discover a handful of useful accessories, and new inventory slots for them, hidden behind a cloud"
	quest.2742EF745632141A.title: "New Trinkets"
	quest.278D34BBC13356DF.quest_desc: [
		"A bruised, purple haze hangs over this unique bog, where the very earth seems stained by corruption. "
		""
		"This volatile landscape is heavily choked with ink-black mushrooms and choked with pooling reservoirs of Virulent Mix, waiting for the careless traveler to misstep."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_ink.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.278D34BBC13356DF.title: "Ink Mushroom Bog"
	quest.283AB56F81EF03A5.quest_desc: ["In order to power your &6Electric Rails&r and your &eElectric Locomotive&r you'll need &eFrames. Frames&r need to be powered and will move power to each connected to &eFrame&r."]
	quest.2869AB982799CF0C.quest_desc: ["The &cOne Way Track Kit&r is quite simple. &7Carts&r can only go where the arrow is facing."]
	quest.291AF252E3415CC1.quest_desc: [
		"Utilizing the stabilization field of &eEziveus' Spectral Compulsion&r, you can expose a myriad of mundane, organic overworld blocks to the essence of the Otherworld. This process breaks down their botanical matrices, refining the plant matter into a highly concentrated &2Nature Paste&r."
		""
		"Once harvested from the center of the infusion circle, combine this viscous paste with your standard Impure White Chalk in a crafting grid. The organic concentrate will permanently dye and reprogram the medium, allowing you to finalize the manufacture of your first sticks of Green Chalk."
	]
	quest.291AF252E3415CC1.quest_subtitle: "Imbuing baseline flora into concentrated alchemical pastes."
	quest.291AF252E3415CC1.title: "Organic Extraction: &2Green Chalk&r"
	quest.295DA5B88AC567AE.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.29953CDAA8A3B0B6.quest_desc: [
		"This operation marks the final entry in the Abras ritual sequence, engineered to breach the deep layers of the Otherworld and pull a top-tier, highly volatile &9Marid&r fire spirit across the planar barrier."
		""
		"This matrix functions as a direct combat challenge. Because the ritual lacks any compliance overrides, the entity cannot be &9bind&r-shackled to an inventory; you must terminate it manually the moment it manifests."
		""
		"To initiate the circle, dress your peripheral bowls with the required reagents, stand back, and throw a Trident directly into your central Golden Sacrificial Bowl. The weapon will be consumed upon impact, instantly starting the ritual and spawning the hostile target into your arena."
	]
	quest.29953CDAA8A3B0B6.quest_subtitle: "Sacrificing forged weaponry to ignite a volatile, high-density elemental rift."
	quest.29953CDAA8A3B0B6.title: "Planar Concussion: The &9Marid&r Breach"
	quest.2A20000FAEC2E16A.quest_desc: ["To extract power or items from your reactor, or even input fuel, you'll need these &crequired&r blocks.\\n\\nThe &cPower Tap&r provides a way for you to \"tap\" into the power that a &9passive&r reactor makes. You can attach pipes and cables to extract the power from it.\\n\\nThe &aAccess Ports&r are required for every reactor, and allows you to both input fuel from the reactor, or extract waste. It's usually a good idea to have 2 per reactor, one for each job."]
	quest.2A20000FAEC2E16A.title: "Interacting with the Reactor"
	quest.2A30595DC6DDBFF7.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Electric Tracks&r are used for the &eElectric Locomotives&r. They'll need to be powered by &eFrames&r and yes it will hurt you if you touch it."
		""
		""
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_electric_rail.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.2AC8314F7AA00426.quest_desc: ["Build a portal out of glowstone and activate it with water!"]
	quest.2AC8314F7AA00426.quest_subtitle: "Use the book of lore to explore items"
	quest.2AF31F1769085641.quest_desc: [
		"The &aReprocessor&r is a 3x3x7 multiblock structure that has specific rules to complete the construction of the multiblock."
		""
		"The heart of this multiblock is the &aController&r, and can be placed on any vertical face as long as it isn't on the frame."
	]
	quest.2B27E4E04A628C60.quest_desc: [
		"To overcome the mechanical latency inherent to standard logistical components, an engineer must install specialized tuning sub-processors within the network framework. "
		""
		"The definitive solution for basic latency reduction is the &eSpeed Upgrade&r, an optimization component that directly accelerates the operational cycling frequency of the housing block. "
		""
		"Whether a garrison requires an automated importer to draft resources from field crates at a rapid pace, or demands that manufacturing blocks process complex schematics without delay, this module stands as the primary answer to industrial stagnation."
		""
		"However, when high-volume logistics threaten to bottleneck the main bus line, the &eStack Upgrade&r must be introduced. "
		""
		"This advanced processing matrix completely alters the transfer protocol; rather than shuffling resources through the conduits in slow, individual units, it forces the component to relocate an entire stack of items simultaneously."
		""
		"By meticulously combining these bulk-transfer matrices with kinetic Speed Upgrades, a logistics officer can achieve peak network efficiency, ensuring an uninterrupted flow of materials through the empire's central hubs."
	]
	quest.2B27E4E04A628C60.quest_subtitle: "Section VII: Network Throughput Optimization"
	quest.2B27E4E04A628C60.title: "Efficiency Integration: &eKinetic Acceleration Modules"
	quest.2C5A7E4CD8B57E08.quest_desc: ["The Grongle Trees endure as the towering, monolithic pillars of the Gronglegrowth biomes, their massive trunks defying the limits of the sky. \\n\\nThey are ancient titans born of a wild, primordial soil—and it is high within their tangled branches that the elusive &eGronglets&r make their home, hidden far above the forest floor."]
	quest.2C8A8B315B4EC99B.quest_desc: [
		"A worm farm is a block you can craft to obtain worms that can be used as bait for fishing."
		""
		"You can use any of the same items that can be used in the composter."
		""
		"Just right click on the worm farm with an empty hand or a non-compostable item to get the worms out."
	]
	quest.2CFEE04BA574921E.quest_desc: [
		"When an engineering outpost demands the automated projection of physical barriers or structural architecture without manual labor, a technician must deploy the &bConstructor&r interface."
		""
		"This specialized directional mechanism materializes data into tangible matter, automatically placing a designated block into the physical world in the exact direction its emitter nozzle is pointed. "
		""
		"To govern its architectural output, an engineer must interface with the unit’s central graphical terminal to hardcode the precise block ID intended for manifestation. "
		""
		"It stands as an invaluable asset for fortress sustainability, allowing defensive walls to automatically re-forge themselves or enabling automated stone generators to continuously feed the colony's expanding borders."
	]
	quest.2CFEE04BA574921E.quest_subtitle: "Section X: Physical World Construction Interfaces"
	quest.2CFEE04BA574921E.title: "&bMatter Fabrication&r: Automated Block Placement"
	quest.2D00F85379A4D591.quest_desc: ["The Item Loader is the most basic dispenser from RailCraft. It has to be above the &6Track&r and can be configured to what you'll want loaded onto your &7Carts&r below."]
	quest.2D592669F4D41793.quest_desc: ["Just like the Reactor, the frame must be built out of &dCasings&r, but the walls can be &9Turbine Glass&r instead!"]
	quest.2D592669F4D41793.title: "Glass Case"
	quest.2D7161D9084B377B.quest_desc: [
		"Executing &6Abras' Open Commanding Conjure&r programs your ritual field to forcefully tether a volatile &cAfrit&r fire spirit directly into the physical mass of an overworld pig. Because your facility performs this ceremony without the structural stabilization field of Red Chalk, the grid's containment parameters are severely compromised—meaning the matrix is only strong enough to manifest a highly aggressive, &9unbound&r entity."
		""
		"Upon triggering the circle, the host organism will rapidly mutate into an &cAfrit&r-possessed Zombified Piglin. You must engage and terminate this creature in close-quarters combat to harvest its corrupted tissue samples. Collecting its dropped Demonic Meat is critical, as this organic byproduct acts as the primary chemical binding agent required to forge your Pink Chalk runic modifiers."
		""
		"&4WARNING: THE EXTRADIMENSIONAL HARVEST YIELDS ARE VARIABLE; YOU WILL LIKELY NEED TO CYCLE THIS RITUAL MATRIX MULTIPLE TIMES TO SECURE AN ADEQUATE QUANTITY OF DEMONIC MEAT FOR YOUR OPERATIONS.&r"
	]
	quest.2D7161D9084B377B.quest_subtitle: "Bypassing stabilization thresholds to force hostile biological drops."
	quest.2D7161D9084B377B.title: "Uncontrolled Mutation: &6Abras' Open Commanding Conjure&r"
	quest.2E2811D1A0F2A492.quest_desc: [
		"As an outpost expands its tactical perimeter, the standard signal field emitted by a basic broadcasting tower will rapidly deteriorate, leaving scouting parties disconnected from the mainframe."
		""
		"To push back these spatial boundaries and stretch your network's data waves across a wider territory, an engineer must forge specialized &bRange Upgrades&r."
		""
		"These sub-processing frequency boosters slide directly into the transmission matrix to amplify signal propagation."
		""
		"However, the internal architecture of the hardware enforces a strict physical limitation: the Wireless Transmitter can only hold 4 total upgrades within its expansion bay. "
		""
		"Meticulously capping the array at this peak operational threshold grants the absolute maximum possible wireless radius allowed before the circuitry risks catastrophic energy feedback."
	]
	quest.2E2811D1A0F2A492.quest_subtitle: "Section XXIX: Wireless Signal Optimization"
	quest.2E2811D1A0F2A492.title: "Range Amplification: Broadcast Boundary Expansion"
	quest.2E596B5A4EA2ABF4.quest_desc: [
		"A careless traveler might easily mistake a resting &3S'Mog&r for a stationary smog vent, only realizing their error when the stone itself begins to breathe. "
		""
		"This elusive entity stands as a close, deceptive cousin to the notorious &2Mog&r, perfectly mimicking its predatory habits, movement patterns, and hostile instincts. "
		""
		"They share an identical, aggressive nature, yet the true distinction lies within their thick hides. "
		""
		"Upon its destruction, a fallen &3S'Mog&r may surrender a harvest of Blue Mogmoss—a rare, glowing fiber highly valued by survivalists."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_smog.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.2E596B5A4EA2ABF4.title: "&3S'Mog&r"
	quest.2FE6737D0DF28142.quest_desc: [
		"If you prefer to delay the dangerous construction parameters required to bind a high-tier &9Marid Crusher&r for your &bLight Blue Chalk&r components, you can deploy an intermediate &aDjinni Crusher&r as an efficient stopgap."
		""
		"To manifest this tier of entity, you must construct the pentacle for &aOphyx' Calling&r. This multi-block matrix acts as your primary anchor for binding &aDjinnis&r to physical vessel frameworks. From a manufacturing standpoint, these spirits operate at a significantly higher throughput than lower-tier Foliots, though they still lag behind the extreme operational speeds of advanced &cAfrits&r or &9Marids&r."
		""
		"Beyond baseline speed upgrades, Djinni-class thralls possess unique thermal dampening properties: they are fully capable of crushing dense ice blocks into packed materials without generating the ambient friction heat that would otherwise melt the resources into waste fluid."
	]
	quest.2FE6737D0DF28142.quest_subtitle: "Scaling processing speed and temperature-controlled crushing lines."
	quest.2FE6737D0DF28142.title: "Mid-Tier Automation: &aOphyx' Calling&r"
	quest.30582B5FBED35FD1.quest_desc: [
		"The volatile element known as &cUtherium&r can only be introduced into the armory through two distinct methods of material acquisition. "
		""
		"Prosperous excavators can locate its raw veins crystallizing within the deep strata, requiring precise extraction directly from the ancient rock faces. "
		""
		"Alternatively, the mineral displays a parasitic affinity with the forces of the blight; it is heavily hoarded within the tissue of wild &cRot Mobs&r, allowing vanguard units to bypass traditional mining operations entirely and plunder the unrefined shards directly from the carcasses of fallen monsters."
	]
	quest.30582B5FBED35FD1.title: "&cUtheric&r"
	quest.30700E99091B712A.quest_desc: [
		"To maintain an absolute equilibrium across a colony's manufacturing line without manual intervention, a technician must implement the &cRegulator Upgrade&r. "
		""
		"This advanced processing matrix allows an engineer to enforce a strict quota of specific items within an adjacent block's physical inventory. "
		""
		"A premier deployment of this mechanism involves affixing it to an Exporter attached to a defense furnace, calibrating the internal register to a fixed value of 64."
		""
		"The network bus line will dynamically monitor the container, automatically pushing fuel tokens whenever the inventory drops beneath the mandated threshold."
		""
		"However, should the required resource exhaust itself from the primary digital vaults, the network will bottleneck unless the &6Crafting Upgrade&r is introduced to the same terminal link."
		""
		"If a valid manufacturing blueprint is logged inside a network Autocrafter, this secondary module authorizes the system to automatically initialize on-demand fabrication loops the moment local reserves fail."
		""
		"Consider a dynamic synthesis scenario: a facility operates a highly automated &aMystical Agriculture&r field, funneling raw Coal Essence into the main database. "
		""
		"By writing the refinement recipe into an active Autocrafter and pairing both upgrades within the furnace's Exporter node, a closed feedback loop is achieved."
		""
		"If the central reserves are completely drained of fuel, the Crafting Upgrade bypasses the shortage—ordering the system to immediately synthesize fresh coal from raw essence to satisfy the Regulator's strict quota.\""
	]
	quest.30700E99091B712A.quest_subtitle: "Section XII: Automated Regulation and On-Demand Manufacturing"
	quest.30700E99091B712A.title: "Logical Logistics: Complementary Network Feedback Loops"
	quest.30869148EDA52DBB.quest_desc: ["The leaves turn orange in the centre."]
	quest.30869148EDA52DBB.title: "Find the Dark Forest Centre"
	quest.31094CC16E710040.quest_desc: [
		"The &4Crowbar&r is the main tool of RailCraft. "
		""
		"When used on a &5Locomotive&r it will change the direction it's facing. "
		""
		"When shift clicked you can connect &5Locomotives&r and &7Carts&r. "
		""
		"When just used on &7Carts&r they give them a slight push. "
		""
		"And when used on special tracks they change their mode. "
		""
		"The different &4Crowbars&r just give different looks and damage."
	]
	quest.32BF2E4192A2652C.quest_desc: ["Even the ground has changed, it seems those changes go beyond just the surface."]
	quest.32BF2E4192A2652C.quest_subtitle: "Be careful while harvesting!"
	quest.32BF2E4192A2652C.title: "Faster Sand"
	quest.32DB907C440E77A0.quest_desc: [
		"Step 7: Miner"
		""
		"Stone and ores are another major need for any colony, so a Mine is the next logical step."
	]
	quest.34CD54347E9821B5.quest_desc: ["Once you make your first Data Model, you'll need to level it up to be useful.\\n\\nData Models start out at the first tier: &7Faulty&r. You'll need to at least level it to &aBasic&r if you'd like to run some simulations on it!\\n\\nOnce placed inside of the Deep Learner, the HUD will tell you how many kills are required to level it up. You can also see this info in the tooltip of the Model itself."]
	quest.34CD54347E9821B5.title: "Leveling Up Data Models"
	quest.34D15631537C26AE.quest_desc: [
		"Consuming &cDemon's Dream Fruit&r is completely safe for mortal consumption, though you must prepare for its distinct metaphysical side effects."
		""
		"Consuming &cDemon's Dream Fruit&r is completely safe for mortal consumption, though you must prepare for its distinct metaphysical side effects."
		""
		"Ingesting the crop temporarily grants you the &3Third Eye&r status effect, piercing the veil of reality to reveal hidden geometry within &9The Otherworld&r. While active, your heightened vision will expose secret resources disguised as standard blocks—such as uncovering hidden groves and mineral deposits necessary for your early progression."
		""
		"Alternatively, you can bypass this manual foraging process entirely. Igniting the fruit inside a dedicated brazier or casting it into a fire source will trigger an immediate alchemical reaction, allowing you to bypass the need for direct sensory sight to gather these materials. The choice of methodology is entirely yours."
	]
	quest.34D15631537C26AE.title: "&cDemons Tasty Fruit"
	quest.34E8AE9BB4D37DA7.quest_desc: ["Get it by killing an Elder Guardian."]
	quest.34E8AE9BB4D37DA7.quest_subtitle: "Dropped by Elder Guardians"
	quest.353AEEC116A5DEEF.quest_desc: [
		"The Ancient Seas are wide-open waters within the &2&lUndergarden&r."
		""
		"Miraculously, despite the heavy pollutants, the water is entirely safe to drink."
		""
		"These depths are home to &bGwibs&r and &bGwiblings&r—and, of course, you can't forget Glitterkelp"
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_ancient.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.353AEEC116A5DEEF.title: "Ancient Sea"
	quest.354086C858E10154.quest_desc: [
		"Now that we have some Cyanite from our baby reactor, we'll want a way to reprocess that waste into something useful."
		""
		"To do this, we'll need to build another multiblock: the &aReprocessor&r."
		""
		"This takes a lot of Cyanite, so start stocking up! You might want to upgrade to a bigger reactor as well. "
	]
	quest.354086C858E10154.title: "Reprocessing Waste"
	quest.36389696767EFB4E.quest_desc: [
		"True to its name, the Barren Abyss is utterly desolate, housing nothing but hostile creatures and scattered pebbles. "
		""
		"Frankly, you are better off looking for pebbles anywhere else..."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_barren.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.36389696767EFB4E.title: "Barren Abyss"
	quest.364408AECE83B5E8.quest_desc: [
		"Constantly generating and shifting multi-block runic layouts places an extreme operational strain on the physical durability of your chalk inventory. To prevent your factory lines from grinding to a halt due to broken tools, you must implement a sustainable maintenance cycle."
		""
		"By channeling the essence of a bound &aDijinni&r through a specialized restoration matrix, you can instantly cleanse, repair, and restore any colored chalk variant back to 100% operational durability. Utilizing this ritual loop entirely bypasses the need to repeat the multi-step raw material smelting and Spiritfire purification processes required to manufacture brand-new sticks from scratch."
		""
		"Alternatively, if you prefer to eliminate tool degradation from your logistics network entirely, you can apply a cross-mod optimization. Bonding an &aEternal Stella&r from the Forbidden \\& Arcanus mod to your chalk items will permanently lock their durability meters, rendering your primary scribing tools completely indestructible."
	]
	quest.364408AECE83B5E8.quest_subtitle: "Deploying mid-tier entities to negate tool durability degradation."
	quest.364408AECE83B5E8.title: "Resource Sustainability: Chalk Restoration"
	quest.365D4B1DC953D406.quest_desc: ["The &7Cart&r Dispenser will do as the name suggests. It can dispense any &7Carts&r onto the &6Tracks&r in front of it. Needs a Redstone signal to dispense."]
	quest.36C2BEA4A039BE75.quest_desc: ["Eat an Experiment 115."]
	quest.36C2BEA4A039BE75.title: "Mystery Meat?"
	quest.36ED3AE12A48BD4D.quest_desc: [
		"Constructing the final geometric multi-block for &9Xeovrenth Adjure&r grants your facility access to the absolute zenith of &5Possession Rituals&r. While this highly advanced containment circle operates with immense energetic requirements and possesses a highly restricted recipe catalog, its activation unlocks the final tier of automated security and material modification."
		""
		"The matrix operates with two distinct operational profiles:"
		""
		"&o&nCruelty Essence Extraction&r: This high-pressure spiritual binding cycle completely fragments the target organism's vital life energy, distilling it into concentrated Cruelty Essence. This dense, volatile byproduct serves as the primary chemical catalyst strictly required to forge your final Brown Chalk modifiers."
		""
		"&o&nAutonomous Heavy Defense&r: The circle can be utilized to permanently shackle an entity into a high-density metallic chassis, constructing an elite Iesnium Golem. This mechanical sentinel functions as an upgraded, autonomous iron golem framework that possesses complete immunity to traditional durability damage while delivering a significantly amplified kinetic damage output to hostile threats."
	]
	quest.36ED3AE12A48BD4D.quest_subtitle: "Triggering pinnacle organic extraction and indestructible construct assembly."
	quest.36ED3AE12A48BD4D.title: "Absolute Subjugation: &9Xeovrenth Adjure&r"
	quest.36FE3019E97AA3F9.quest_subtitle: "Deafeat glorious warriors in 1 versus 1 combat in preparation for the final battle"
	quest.36FE3019E97AA3F9.title: "Valkyries?"
	quest.3751015CD5C84134.title: "&b4096B Fluid Storage Part"
	quest.37EBB8E0D6E5F821.quest_desc: ["&6Hostile Neural Networks&r (HNN for short) is a mod based around simulating mob kills for loot!\\n\\nTo do this, you will be collecting \"data\" on mobs, then running simulations from the data to create their drops!\\n"]
	quest.37EBB8E0D6E5F821.title: "Welcome to &9Hostile Neural Networks&r!"
	quest.380D3212D1CBA593.quest_desc: [
		"Stepping out from the shadows of the infected hordes comes the &cRotwalker&r, the terrifying, medium-sized vanguard of the corrupted &cRot Mobs&r. "
		""
		"It boasts a grotesque, heavily reinforced vitality equivalent to forty standard measures of health, standing as a durable monument to the spreading blight. "
		""
		"True to the relentless instincts driving all infected &cRot Mobs&r, this walking horror focuses its mindless aggression entirely on tearing down the proud &2Stoneborns&r and the ancient &7Forgottens&r. "
		""
		"Should you successfully survive its brutal assault and cleave through its rotting flesh, its remains will surrender a valuable harvest of &cUtheric Shards&r."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_rotwalker.png width:100 height:200 align:center}"
	]
	quest.380D3212D1CBA593.title: "&cRotwalker&r"
	quest.38451B61E3FC075B.quest_desc: [
		"Wait we have Steel again does that also mean we get our (Coal) Coke back? Yes! \\nTo get (Coal) Coke you'll need a Coke Oven. To make one you'll need 26 Coke Oven Bricks and place them 3x3x3 with 1 block hollow in the center. You'll know it's done when you can access the GUI and it's all one texture. \\n\\nPlace Coal or Coal Blocks to get (Coal) Coke and Liquid Creosote! You can always put any log in to get Charcoal and Creasote."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_coke.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.394C24C83DA2ECFE.quest_desc: ["Found in Jungle Pyramids"]
	quest.394C24C83DA2ECFE.quest_subtitle: "Found in Jungle Pyramid chests"
	quest.3999AE0921641E60.quest_desc: ["&8Dark Matter&r is created by Smelting Edelwood. \\n\\n&5Corrupti Dust&r is made with &5Obsidiansteel&r and some Mob Drops. \\n\\nThrow both these on the ground together and a &8Black Hole&r will spawn! \\n\\nThe &8Black Hole&r will void every Item or Projectile that comes near, but what we want to feed it is &aExperience&r! \\n\\nWhen you feed it enough &aEXP&r it will give back an &aXpetrified Orb&r."]
	quest.39C8E1705EF1CD31.title: "&e256B Fluid Storage Part"
	quest.3AF7446592D19FA6.quest_desc: [
		"The glistening gemstone classified as &eRegalium&r reigns as the definitive equivalent to surface-world emeralds within the boundaries of the &2&lUndergarden&r. "
		""
		"Due to its rigid, brittle crystal lattice, it possesses zero structural malleability and cannot be forged into defensive armor plating or sharp tools at the anvil. "
		""
		"However, it holds supreme economic value as a medium of diplomatic exchange. "
		""
		"When presented to the stoic &2Stoneborns&r, this glittering mineral acts as the primary currency required to open commerce, allowing vanguard units to trade for high-value survival goods and exotic items."
	]
	quest.3AF7446592D19FA6.title: "&eRegalium&r"
	quest.3B84215240D9F2CB.quest_desc: [
		"To protect the integrity of digitized archives from espionage or unauthorized manipulation, an engineer must integrate the &3Security Manager&r into the central grid. "
		""
		"This defensive apparatus allows a commander to dictate precise administrative permissions and network access rules across the garrison. "
		""
		"Operating on an identity-binding matrix, it requires a dedicated &3Security Card&r to be calibrated for each individual player requiring clearance. "
		""
		"Should the manager remain completely devoid of these cards, the network reverts to an open architecture, granting full system rights to anyone who interfaces with the terminal."
		""
		"To enforce a strict blackout protocol against unconfigured personnel, a blank, unbound card must be locked into the manager's core receptacle, instantly revoking general clearance. "
		""
		"No matter the level of security restriction enforced, the architect who physically placed the &3Security Manager&r remains hardcoded into the system, retaining absolute, un-bypassable access to the network at all times."
	]
	quest.3B84215240D9F2CB.quest_subtitle: "Section II: Network Security and Permission Management"
	quest.3B84215240D9F2CB.title: "Defensive Protocol: Access Restriction"
	quest.3BCA33834716DA39.quest_desc: ["Found in Buried Chests."]
	quest.3BCA33834716DA39.quest_subtitle: "Found in Buried Treasure chests"
	quest.3C3FE45CEF5E242B.quest_desc: [
		"While the other &aReprocessor Parts&r have a mandatory spot when building, these three parts can be placed on any vertical face as long as they aren't on the frame!"
		""
		"The &cPower Port&r is used to give power to the multiblock machine to process waste."
		""
		"The &9Fluid Injector Port&r is used to inject the liquid needed, which will depend on the type of waste injected. "
		""
		"For Cyanite, that means water!\\n\\nThe &aOutput Port&r is used to output the reprocessed material. "
		""
		"You can right click it to grab the material out by hand, or pipe it out for automation."
	]
	quest.3C4B6468B14C039E.quest_subtitle: "Take a look at those skyroot buckets, they can't hold lava tho!"
	quest.3C4B6468B14C039E.title: "Buckets made easy"
	quest.3D91D754E66F9811.quest_desc: ["Dropped by Evokers."]
	quest.3D91D754E66F9811.quest_subtitle: "Found in Woodland Mansion chests"
	quest.3E3CBDCEAB0FF28F.quest_desc: ["The &9Deep Learner&r is one of the core components of HNN.\\n\\nWith this item, you can right click to open up a HUD and store &6Data Models&r to gather data while killing mobs.\\n\\nEach Learner can hold 4 Data Models, and as long as you have the Learner anywhere in your inventory, it will collect data for the models placed inside!\\n\\nNote: You can have multiple Deep Learners in your inventory, and it will count the kills for all Data Models inside all of the Learners."]
	quest.3E3CBDCEAB0FF28F.quest_subtitle: "The Learning HUD"
	quest.3E3CBDCEAB0FF28F.title: "&aLearning Mobs"
	quest.3E75AFE3482834C5.quest_desc: [
		"&lRailCraft&r is an entire mod based off &5Trains&r! \\n\\nFrom &7Minecarts&r to &eElectric Locomotives&r to &9Tunnel Bores&r! "
		""
		"It has everything &5Train&r accessory wise as well! "
		""
		"Traffic Lights, Steam Boilers to power &5Trains&r, and automation for it all. "
		""
		"The model Mod for Model &5Train&r Lovers!"
	]
	quest.3E75AFE3482834C5.title: "Railcraft Reborn"
	quest.3E890BABC4C41370.quest_desc: [
		"As an outpost expands across the frontier, relying on physical cabling to bridge distant substations becomes an engineered structural liability. "
		""
		"To circumvent the logistical limits of the central &3Controller&r without weaving a chaotic labyrinth of wiring, a technician must establish a wireless data frequency. "
		""
		"This specialized long-range relay relies entirely on the precise pairing of a &3Network Transmitter&r and a &3Network Receiver&r."
		""
		"The structural protocol commands that the &9Transmitter&r be integrated directly into the primary bus line adjacent to the central Controller hub. "
		""
		"Conversely, the matching &9Receiver&r must be anchored at the localized periphery—whether it be a subterranean insect apiary, an automated monster culling chamber, or a distant processing facility. "
		""
		"To bridge the spatial void between these nodes, an uncalibrated &3Network Card&r is required. "
		""
		"The mechanic must first execute a firm right-click action upon the remote Receiver to permanently burn its coordinates into the card's memory matrix, and then slide that bound card directly into the central Transmitter's receptacle to anchor the frequency."
	]
	quest.3E890BABC4C41370.quest_subtitle: "Section IV: Wireless Network Extension"
	quest.3E890BABC4C41370.title: "Signal Bridge: Detached Terminal Frequency"
	quest.3E8C2E7769DFBF35.quest_desc: [
		"Unlike the &3Steam Locomotive&r you won't need to put anything into the &eElectric Locomotive&r. \\n\\nIt runs off the power from the &eFrames&r beneath the &6Electric Tracks&r. \\n\\nYes, it can only be ran off &6Electric Tracks&r."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_electric.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.3F8EEE1AD4420702.title: "&b64k Storage Part"
	quest.3F9D553C9FA64F2A.quest_desc: ["Reactors are multi-block structures, meaning you can create your own custom size!\\n\\nIf you're using &aBasic Reactor Parts&r, the largest size reactor you can build is 5x5x5.\\n\\nThe &lBiggest&r Reactor that you can make using &eReinforced Reactor Parts&r is 32x32x48. There are a lot of variables that contribute to the overall output of a reactor, so make sure to experiment!\\n\\nSome overall tips:\\n\\nThe taller the reactor, the more fuel it can hold and burn because there are more fuel rods, meaning more overall power. This also means a higher &cburn rate&r.\\n\\nThe wider the reactor, the more efficient it is, as long as you don't add more fuel rods to the design. This means less consumption overall."]
	quest.3F9D553C9FA64F2A.title: "Expanding The Reactor"
	quest.3FD801D7DE9176FB.title: "&e4k Storage Part"
	quest.403271A8740E9141.quest_desc: [
		"The volatile oils within &cDemon's Dream Fruit&r possess highly exotic, flammable properties."
		""
		"Casting the crop onto the ground and igniting it with a flint and steel will manifest a localized patch of &dSpiritfire&r. This stable, ethereal flame acts as your primary alchemical catalyst, stripping away earthly illusions to transform mundane overworld items into true &9Otherworld&r components."
		""
		"The resulting purple fire emits no heat to the surrounding environment, serving as a visually striking, permanent focal point for your automation room."
	]
	quest.403271A8740E9141.title: "&9The Otherworldly&r Flames"
	quest.403A4FCD9ECB1282.quest_desc: [
		"Scaling the resource capacity of your sub-spatial storage network requires anchoring specialized &dStorage Stabilizers&r to your central matrix."
		""
		"To initialize the connection, these stabilizing pylons must face and point directly at the floating Dimensional Matrix core hovering above your Storage Actuator, rather than the mechanical base block itself. The stabilizers can be positioned up to a maximum distance of 5 blocks away, but they require a completely unobstructed, clear line of sight to the matrix core to sustain the field."
		""
		"When upgrading your network to a higher-tier stabilizer, breaking an active pylon will not destroy or drop your stored commodities. However, removing a stabilizer instantly downscales your total slot allowance; you will be completely locked out from depositing any new materials into the system until a valid stabilizing field is restored or upgraded."
		""
		"Refer to the visual schematic below for an example of a validated spatial configuration."
	]
	quest.403A4FCD9ECB1282.title: "Matrix Expansion: &dStorage Stabilizers&r"
	quest.406737E4C4072AB9.title: "Slay a Naga"
	quest.4071BBBE12CACD2D.quest_desc: ["The &5Train&r Dispenser is a better version of the &7Cart&r Dispenser. It can Dispense the whole &5Locomotive&r and more! Set a pattern for what you want to be deployed then give it a redstone signal."]
	quest.4101F8275B41C79B.title: "&61k Storage Part"
	quest.4141EF8B8C316118.quest_desc: [
		"&7Cloggrum&r reigns undisputed as the foundational iron of the &2&lUndergarden&r, serving as the absolute bedrock of subterranean craftsmanship. "
		""
		"Its dense veins permeate nearly every strata of the earth, ensuring that diligent excavators will encounter it throughout their travels. "
		""
		"This highly adaptable mineral serves as a critical catalyst, bound into a vast multitude of structural, defensive, and alchemical recipes. "
		""
		"Its presence is so deeply woven into the dimension's biology that even certain ravenous entities have absorbed its raw shards into their flesh, surrendering unrefined chunks of the metal upon their destruction."
	]
	quest.4141EF8B8C316118.title: "&7Cloggrum&r"
	quest.41B4C7B9D3AE6317.quest_desc: ["Craft it using a witch's pupil"]
	quest.41EDEF510157A6F8.quest_desc: [
		"This operation marks the culmination of the Abras sequence. The ceremony is engineered to pull a top-tier, highly volatile &9Marid&r fire spirit across the planar barrier. Even though your geometric foundation now integrates the containment field of Red Chalk, the raw energetic output of this entity still surpasses the grid's suppression limits. Because the matrix cannot fully &9bind&r the entity into immediate submission, you must prepare for a high-intensity combat encounter to terminate it manually."
		""
		"This ceremony features a distinct departure from standard possession logic by utilizing a forged Trident as the focal sacrifice rather than a living creature. Because there is no biological organism to execute over the runes, the ignition criteria must be triggered kinetically."
		""
		"Once your peripheral bowls are properly dressed with their material reagents, you must manually throw the Trident directly at the central Golden Sacrificial Bowl. Impacting the core anchor will instantly shatter the weapon, consuming its structural integrity to spark the summoning matrix and manifest the hostile entity."
	]
	quest.41EDEF510157A6F8.quest_subtitle: "Bypassing biological anchors through focal metallic sacrifices."
	quest.41EDEF510157A6F8.title: "Kinetic Ignition: The &9Marid&r Breakthrough"
	quest.4204538C06CA4F3A.quest_subtitle: "It seems the skyroot bucket can be used to harvest a poison like substance from those small poisonous plants, to achieve a similar effect to a cockatrice attack"
	quest.422F020921C08527.quest_desc: ["Plant the magic beans on some Uberous Soil, then climb the beanstalk to one of the floating cloud cottages slay a giant and obtain a giant pickaxe."]
	quest.425E375A9EC127EB.quest_desc: [
		"&6Reinforced Tracks&r are the upgraded version of normal &6rails&r! They're slightly faster and don't blow up."
		""
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_reinforced1.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
		""
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_reinforced2.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
		""
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_reinforced3.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
		""
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_reinforced4.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.42D2E85CD0BF6D1F.quest_desc: ["Not essential, but very helpful for finding your way around."]
	quest.43A1BC20BB054A14.quest_desc: [
		"\"Deep within the freezing depths of the Ancient and Icy Seas thrives the elusive Glitterkelp. "
		""
		"While it appears entirely passive—doing little more than casting a soft, bioluminescent glow through the dark currents—it holds a prized status among coastal gatherers. "
		""
		"When carefully harvested and drained of its briny fluids, this radiant flora can be baked into a rare, glowing pastry known to travelers as Glitterkelp Pie. "
		""
		"It is a dish celebrated as much for its eerie, shifting light as it is for its unique sweetness."
	]
	quest.43E8912CB307E421.quest_desc: [
		"While securing an empire's assets virtually within digital media blocks completely reorganizes physical vault space, a commander requires a functional viewport to access and command the stockpile. "
		""
		"To lift the veil and expose the contents of the active database, an engineer must construct the standardized &3Grid&r terminal."
		""
		"This mechanism functions as the essential, foundational 'Display' for your facility, projecting a real-time visual index of all digitized resources currently locked within the network bus line."
		""
		"The computational bandwidth of this central interface is remarkably broad, allowing a single terminal screen to monitor, sort, and withdraw six distinct matter formats seamlessly: tangible Items, pressurized Fluids, raw electrical Energy, mystical Source catalysts, captured Souls, and high-risk alchemical Chemicals."
	]
	quest.43E8912CB307E421.quest_subtitle: "Section XVIII: The Central Information Display Grid"
	quest.43E8912CB307E421.title: "User Interaction: Data-Core Visualization"
	quest.43FD4AEBB9548E57.quest_desc: [
		"Deeply entwined with its neighboring swamplands, the Smogstem Forest shares the same unnatural blue coloration and clusters of Indigo Mushrooms. "
		""
		"Yet, as the bog recedes, the terrain shifts into a towering labyrinth dominated by massive, overgrown Smogstem Trees that block out what little light remains."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_smogstem.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.43FD4AEBB9548E57.title: "Smogstem Forest"
	quest.4415C9F8DA2D7E68.quest_desc: [
		"With Cyanite, we can create the heart of the Turbine, the &9Turbine Controller&r."
		""
		"Turbines are multi-block structures, just like Reactors! "
		""
		"They input vapors like &7Steam&r made by &dActively Cooled&r Reactors to create TONS of power! "
		""
		"We'll need a few other pieces to be able to build our first one."
		""
		"Note: Basic Turbine parts can only be used to build a max size Turbine of 5x5x10. "
		""
		"To build a bigger Turbine, you must use &aReinforced Turbine Parts&r."
	]
	quest.4415C9F8DA2D7E68.title: "Creating Turbines"
	quest.44881E39AB1D62AA.quest_desc: [
		"To transform encoded blueprints into tangible military assets, an engineer must deploy the &3Autocrafter&r."
		""
		"This hardware block acts as the primary repository where programmed Patterns are stored, allowing the central grid to index exactly how to forge complex items."
		""
		"Once a master schematic is secured within the machine's terminal bays, a commander can remotely initiate a material 'Request' directly from any central &3Grid&r terminal. "
		""
		"Activating this remote requisition protocol requires the operator to execute a precise keystroke sequence, pressing Control + Shift while clicking the targeted item icon to summon the manufacturing registry interface."
		""
		"Beyond standard immediate assembly, this mechanism can be oriented facing a physical machine to implement advanced &6Processing Patterns&r."
		""
		"For example, aligning the output face of the &3Autocrafter&r directly toward a blast furnace allows the system to manage complex thermal refinement recipes, such as smelting Raw Processors into finished components. "
		""
		"So long as the Crafter remains wired to the main network bus line and the furnace is equipped with an input Importer to siphon the refined items back into digital storage, the network will seamlessly process the order. "
		""
		"This enables a logistics officer to request the fully smelted variation of a resource with a single click, completely automating the colony's industrial foundries."
	]
	quest.44881E39AB1D62AA.quest_subtitle: "Section XXIII: The Autocrafter and Processing Networks"
	quest.44881E39AB1D62AA.title: "Manufacturing Terminal: Schematic Execution Hubs"
	quest.45317C2150B7879A.quest_subtitle: "This gem has a perplexing quality, with lower durability certain qualities strenghten themselves, such as armor becomes more durable"
	quest.4568C2F465EDB960.quest_desc: [
		"The resilience of the Droopfruit is a marvel of the underworld, defying territorial boundaries to take root across nearly every biome. "
		""
		"To find them, one must cast their gaze away from the soil and search the high stone ceilings. "
		""
		"They cling tightly to the rocky vaults of the world, anchoring themselves to the overhead bedrock and cascading downward in luminescent strands that mirror the glowing flora of the ancient subterranean depths."
	]
	quest.45CEDDB7FDD0276F.quest_desc: [
		"Your next logistical evolution requires a transition into &6Infusion Rituals&r. Unlike traditional summoning circles that manifest entities into physical space, these hybrid matrices are engineered to permanently siphon and imbue the essence of otherworldly spirits straight into physical components."
		""
		"The foundational matrix for this discipline is &eEziveus' Spectral Compulsion&r. This entry-tier configuration acts as your primary alchemical forge, allowing you to manufacture several core components and advanced alloys that are strictly mandatory throughout your upcoming progression."
		""
		"Because each distinct ritual discipline scales backward-compatibly with its own independent upgrade path, it is critical to construct this layout inside a separate, dedicated zone away from your primary summoning perimeters to avoid overlapping geometric errors."
	]
	quest.45CEDDB7FDD0276F.quest_subtitle: "Permanently binding spirit properties into material components."
	quest.45CEDDB7FDD0276F.title: "Ethereal Synthesis: &6Infusion Rituals&r"
	quest.46CB1AAE1BB94F87.quest_desc: ["Lootr makes it possible for everyone to get loot not just the first person. No more rushing out to horde all the loot. Win-Win!"]
	quest.46CB1AAE1BB94F87.quest_subtitle: "Discover Loot"
	quest.46DCB235D3FEDA61.quest_desc: [
		"These specialized implements match the fundamental capabilities of standard iron gear, yet they harbor a passive, cryogenic enchantment within their forged edges. "
		""
		"Upon delivering a successful strike, the weapon instantly leaches heat from the target's flesh, inflicting a freezing lethality that severely slows the movement and reflex speed of any hostile entity it cuts down. "
		""
		"The only exception to this crippling enchantment rests within the agricultural hoe, which lacks the necessary surface area to channel the frostbite—though an authentic warrior has little use for a farming tool when standing on the front lines of a frantic skirmish."
	]
	quest.46DCB235D3FEDA61.title: "&bFroststeel&r Tools"
	quest.4710379C44BA78C9.quest_desc: [
		"Deploying your newly bound &9Marid Crusher&r opens the gateway to fracturing hyper-dense, sound-attuned materials that lower-tier processing thralls would simply shatter into useless fragments."
		""
		"Your immediate logistical objective requires feeding a raw Echo Shard into your master spirit's crushing matrix. The entity will rapidly pulverize the shard into a highly specialized resonance powder."
		""
		"Once harvested, take this acoustic catalyst to any standard crafting grid and combine it directly with a refined Iesnium Ingot and a luminous Glow Ink Sac. The glow properties will permanently bind the energetic vibrations of the echo particles to the dense metallic substrate, completing the intricate chemical synthesis required to forge your Cyan Chalk modifiers."
	]
	quest.4710379C44BA78C9.quest_subtitle: "Fragmenting deep-slate vibrations to bind late-game colored modifiers."
	quest.4710379C44BA78C9.title: "Resonance Coupling: Cyan Chalk"
	quest.4745152F6FF242B3.quest_desc: ["When the reactor burns up fuel, it creates &9waste&r or a &dReactant&r that you'll also want to extract. That is what the other Solid Access Port is for! Make sure to set it to output, then pipe it into some type of storage."]
	quest.4745152F6FF242B3.title: "Waste Not"
	quest.4756A1D3F1F9F5B2.quest_subtitle: "This machine incubates wild moas eggs, a new mount for you!"
	quest.475E307844E3AF7F.quest_desc: [
		"The Water Boilers are some of the most helpful machines from &l&7RailCraft&r. They need a Fuel Firebox and some sort of boiler on top. The Fueled Firebox can be 1x1 2x2 or 3x3. The size of the Firebox changes how big the Boiler on top can be. For 1x1 Firebox it can only have 1x1 Boiler. For 2x2 Firebox it can be a 2x2x3 Boiler. For 3x3 Firebox it can be 3x3x4. The Liquid Fuel will take Creosote to heat up. For Solid Firebox it'll use anything a furnace can use."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_big_boiler.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.476755275B948A5F.quest_desc: [
		"Reactors can also be used to heat up &bcoolants&r like water to create &bvapor&r, like &bSteam&r."
		""
		"To do this, you'll need to build a reinforced reactor. "
		""
		"This is built in the same way that you built your 3x3x3 reactor, but all of the parts will need to be &aReinforced Reactor Parts&r instead. "
		""
		"I'd also suggest on it being bigger than a 3x3x3."
		""
		"To input a coolant, you'll need a &9Forge Fluid Port&r. "
		""
		"This will port in any fluids like Water into the reactor. This will also be used to export the vapor created in the reactor."
	]
	quest.476755275B948A5F.title: "Actively Cooled Reactor"
	quest.47732892296BD6FE.quest_desc: [
		"Reaching the absolute pinnacle of occult geometry requires you to forge a foundation medium capable of anchoring the most volatile entities in the cosmos. Utilizing the dense containment field of &cSevira's Permanent Confinement&r, you can force highly unstable skeletal catalysts to fuse with terrestrial alloys."
		""
		"By compressing a complex arrangement of Wither-derived materials alongside pure Netherite plates inside the infusion circle, the matrix will yield three units of Witherite Dust. This synthetic metamaterial possesses unmatched particle density; combine it directly with your existing chalk inventory in a crafting grid to complete the manufacture of your first sticks of Black Chalk."
		""
		"Securing this midnight-black foundation completes your alchemical toolkit, permanently unlocking the structural parameters required to layout the highest tiers of Marid-class summoning grids."
	]
	quest.47732892296BD6FE.quest_subtitle: "Stabilizing cataclysmic compounds into the highest form of foundation geometry."
	quest.47732892296BD6FE.title: "The Ultimate Medium: Black Chalk"
	quest.48867549FFD29F2E.quest_subtitle: "These trees do not hold gold but a new substances, amber. Amber is very useful for making a new type of ranged weapon."
	quest.48867549FFD29F2E.title: "Gold in Trees?"
	quest.49D1C02DA93922F4.quest_desc: [
		"You can store fishing related items and fish bait in one of these."
		"The Tackle Box is also where you can attatch equipment to the fishing rods."
	]
	quest.49EB9FB2133E3219.quest_desc: [
		"The tattered plating designated as Ancient Armor serves as the standard martial uniform worn exclusively by the skeletal &7Forgottens&r patrolling the tombs. "
		""
		"Because the secrets of forging this specific alloy have been completely lost to time, the armor cannot be shaped at a modern anvil; it must be systematically stripped from their shattered frames upon their definitive fall in battle. "
		""
		"Remarkably, the full defensive set contains a permanent structural vacancy: there is no historical record or physical blueprint for Ancient Boots. "
		""
		"Extensive skeletal examinations reveal a bizarre anatomical anomaly, as the tomb-dwelling &7Forgottens&r are completely devoid of feet, floating or dragging across the stone without the need for footwear."
	]
	quest.49EB9FB2133E3219.title: "Ancient Armor"
	quest.4A08245126368C0C.quest_desc: ["Use and break a Glass Sword."]
	quest.4A08245126368C0C.title: "One Hit Wonder"
	quest.4A11729731A3ED72.quest_desc: [
		"Utilizing the advanced synthesis field of &aStrigeor's Higher Binding&r, you can successfully manufacture a batch of Gray Paste. This dense, chemically altered substance contains highly focused extra-dimensional energy."
		""
		"Once extracted from your infusion array, combine this paste with a standard stick of Impure White Chalk in any crafting grid. The compound will thoroughly saturate the material, permanently altering its chemical signature to complete the manufacture of your Gray Chalk modifiers."
	]
	quest.4A11729731A3ED72.quest_subtitle: "Infusing high-density pastes into baseline ritual mediums."
	quest.4A11729731A3ED72.title: "Chemical Doping: Gray Chalk"
	quest.4A44623D8A307473.quest_desc: [
		"The &6High Speed Electric Tracks&r are like the &6Electric Tracks&r but faster! They also require what the normal &6High Speed Tracks&r require and what the &6Electric Tracks&r require. &cSpeed Boosts&r and &eFrames&r to power them. Now you have to be careful around corners and with touching them!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_electric_speed.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.4AD8363D7359A072.quest_desc: [
		"We're going to build the smallest passive reactor possible, the &93x3x3&r. The requirements for the quest are the exact amounts for what you'll need to build one.\\n\\nTo build this, you start by building a 3x3x3 frame made out of Casings. In the middle of the bottom face, you can just use another Reactor Casing. You'll want each outer wall to have a &9reactor component&r, like an Active Power Tap or Solid Access Port."
		""
		"Every reactor you build will require exactly 1 &6Reactor Controller&r, which is usually put in the middle of the front wall. Next, we'll place 1 &aFuel Rod&r in the center of the multiblock, and 1 &eControl Rod&r above it on the top face.\\n\\nYou will need a way to input and output waste, which is done by using &9Reactor Solid Access Ports&r. For this build, place one on the left side and one on the right.\\n\\nTo extract power, we'll place the &cActive Power Tap&r on the middle of the back wall. Once placed, the reactor should complete! You can now right click the Controller to open up the interface and turn it on!\\n\\nNote: The biggest reactor you can make using &aBasic Reactor Parts&r is 5x5x5. To build a larger reactor, you will need &eReinforced Reactor Parts&r."
		""
		"This is what a 3x3x3 reactor will look like:\\n"
	]
	quest.4AD8363D7359A072.quest_subtitle: "Learning The Basics"
	quest.4AD8363D7359A072.title: "&dOur First Reactor"
	quest.4B535B3689DF24DF.quest_desc: [
		"The entities waiting in the next tier of progression belong to a volatile class of fire elementals known as &cAfrit Demons&r. These highly advanced spirits possess immense processing power, but their physical compliance scales entirely with the geometric strength of your binding pentacle."
		""
		"Because your current chemical labs lack access to specialized Red Chalk formulas, you cannot construct the high-tier stabilization grids necessary to suppress their willpower. Consequently, any summoning attempt at this stage will manifest an &9Unbound&r Demon."
		""
		"Without a closed command circuit to shackle its instincts, the entity will immediately turn violent upon materialization, forcing you to terminate it manually in close-quarters combat to harvest its latent core components."
	]
	quest.4B535B3689DF24DF.quest_subtitle: "Evaluating containment thresholds and hostile manifestation risks."
	quest.4B535B3689DF24DF.title: "Thermal Instability: &cAfrit Demons&r"
	quest.4B7870B5DBF67428.quest_desc: ["Found in Igloos."]
	quest.4B7870B5DBF67428.quest_subtitle: "Found in Igloo chests"
	quest.4B81E84CAE814BA9.title: "&664B Fluid Storage Part"
	quest.4B9C8C7BAB6C36AF.quest_desc: ["Craft it using an Undead Soul."]
	quest.4B9E9497E44D0096.quest_desc: ["To build a reactor, you'll need to start by making &6Reactor Casings&r.\\n\\nThese make up the frame and walls of your reactor, although the walls can be replaced by &9Reactor Glass&r if you'd like to see inside of your reactor.\\n\\nFor future reference, when a part says \"Basic\", this means that it can only be used with other basic parts. The Basic parts can also only be used to build smaller reactors, as it has a certain size limit. Keep this in mind!"]
	quest.4B9E9497E44D0096.title: "Reactor Building Components"
	quest.4BD97F45798CD89C.quest_desc: [
		"Welcome to the arcane arts of &dOccultism&r."
		""
		"This branch of progression relies on breaching the planar veil to harness the labor of otherworldly &c&mDemons&r &bSpirits&r. These extra-dimensional entities will serve as the backbone of your automated processing networks, performing tireless labor for your factory line. Do not fear their origins; they are perfectly compliant under contractual binding. &oUsually&r."
		""
		"To open your gateway into this discipline, you must harvest raw &aDemon's Dream Seeds&r. Scour the landscape and clear away standard wild grass patches until you uncover a cache of these exotic seeds."
	]
	quest.4BD97F45798CD89C.quest_subtitle: "Step of Beginnings"
	quest.4BD97F45798CD89C.title: "&cDemons&r are &dDreaming"
	quest.4C1A96E1E8A233BA.quest_desc: ["Fishing loot."]
	quest.4C46EF35796A9833.quest_desc: [
		"This codex serves as your primary intelligence briefing on &dRituals&r. Understanding the core classifications is vital before constructing your first containment zones."
		""
		"&lTiers of Rituals&r"
		""
		"Ceremonies are categorized into four primary tiers, dictated by the raw power and instability of the entity you are invoking. Progression scales upward from lesser &eFoliot&r spirits, advancing through &aDjini&r, &cAfrit&r, and culminating in the highly volatile &9Marid&r tier. Highly specialized intermediate tiers—such as the &6Unbound Afrit&r tier—exist for anomalous entities."
		""
		"&lTypes of Rituals&r"
		""
		"While five distinct disciplines exist, your factory progression strictly relies on four. The core methodologies consist of &9Summoning Rituals&r, &5Possession Rituals&r, and &6Infusion Rituals&r, each detailed extensively upon their introduction. The fourth variant comprises &dDemon-less Rituals&r—hybrid matrices that draw upon elements of all three core paths to trigger localized alchemical reactions without binding a physical entity."
		""
		"The final discipline, &eFamiliar Rituals&r, is entirely optional for logistical progression but remains highly valuable if you wish to manifest specialized utility entities to secure unique passive buffs."
		""
		"&lChalks&r"
		""
		"Arcane chalks are divided into two operational classes: Foundation Chalks and Colored Chalks."
		""
		"Foundation variants act as the structural anchors required for every single geometric pentacle. Their tier correlates directly to their density and color, darkening sequentially as you advance from basic &l&f&lWhite&r&r&r Chalk up to midnight &0&lBlack&r&r Chalk."
		""
		"Conversely, &cC&r&6o&r&el&r&ao&r&9r&r&5e&r&dd&r Chalks act as the secondary modifiers that program the ritual's exact parameters. Unlike foundations, a colored chalk's pigment indicates its specific alchemical function rather than a strict power tier."
	]
	quest.4C5CFA45D9B4F6D3.quest_desc: [
		"To hunt for Indigo Mushrooms, one must look to the heavens and seek the sapphire canopies of the Smogstem Trees. "
		""
		"These unique fungi are rarely found wandering alone, preferring instead the dense company of their towering counterparts. "
		""
		"They claim the damp earth around the grey trunks, multipling rapidly within the suffocating fog as if the trees themselves were whispering life directly into the fungal spores."
	]
	quest.4CD83943865018EA.quest_desc: [
		"To automate the outbound distribution of resources from the digital archives to the physical manufacturing lines, an engineer must install the specialized &9Exporter&r interface cable. "
		""
		"This tactical routing mechanism actively pulls designated items from your network storage and forcibly pushes them directly into adjacent physical blocks. "
		""
		"It serves as an invaluable asset for camp sustainability, seamlessly feeding raw unrefined ores or dark fuels directly into the hungry maws of blast furnaces, or routing specific strategic materials into dedicated armory chests. "
		""
		"Furthermore, the unit features an internal filtration matrix, allowing a logistics officer to precisely calibrate exactly which item IDs are permitted to exit the network bus line, preventing system pollution."
	]
	quest.4CD83943865018EA.quest_subtitle: "Section VIII: Targeted Resource Distribution"
	quest.4CD83943865018EA.title: "&9Output Expulsion&r: Direct Material Delivery"
	quest.4D836B9D9E3B898F.quest_desc: [
		"The stoic entities known as &2Stoneborns&r exist as a perfect, harmonious amalgamation of village merchant and iron sentinel. "
		""
		"They possess a deep intelligence and a willingness to cooperate with travelers, eagerly engaging in commerce and trading rare goods with anyone who approaches them with peaceful intent. "
		""
		"Yet, beneath their calm, trading demeanor rests the absolute martial might of a guardian; they will ruthlessly cut down any hostile monsters that threaten their domain, and will instantly turn their immense strength against any foolish traveler who dares to strike them."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_stoneborn.png width:100 height:150 align:center}"
	]
	quest.4D836B9D9E3B898F.title: "&2Stoneborn&r"
	quest.4E3D548E5D8D7D26.quest_desc: [
		"The Forgotten Fields stretch out as the silent, empty plains of the &2&lUndergarden&r. "
		""
		"No trees pierce the horizon, leaving the expanse to the cold earth, weeping flowers, and restless entities. "
		""
		"Yet, the true enigma lies in its name: despite the whispers of the past, no &7Forgotten&r has ever been seen walking these hollow lands."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_field.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.4E3D548E5D8D7D26.title: "Forgotten Fields"
	quest.4ED36AA3766E842B.quest_desc: [
		"Instead of building the smallest Turbine at this point, it's better to build a Turbine based off of the design of your &9Reactor&r."
		""
		"For starters, you want to build a Turbine that can handle the &9Vapor Production Rate&r of your reactor. "
		""
		"To get the most power out of it, it'll need to maintain either 900RPM or 1800RPM as well. "
		""
		"This takes a lot of experimenting with different coils, # of blades, and overall size of the Turbine!"
		""
		"Note: To complete this quest, you'll need to create a &dTask Screen&r of any size. "
		""
		"Once placed, you can right-click the screen and select this quest as the requirement, then output power into the task screen block to fill it up and complete the quest."
	]
	quest.4ED36AA3766E842B.title: "&dThe Turbine"
	quest.4F3B4990BE6C2A4A.quest_desc: [
		"The gentle &7Scintlings&r thrive as the small, innocent gastropods found crawling across nearly every corner of the &2&lUndergarden&r. "
		""
		"They possess a curious trait akin to the fabled snow constructs of the outer worlds, painting the landscape with a continuous, glistening trail of viscous slime wherever they roam. "
		""
		"Upon their tragic demise, their fragile bodies surrender a small cluster of Scintling Goo. "
		""
		"However, because this precious substance can be gathered freely and endlessly from the residue of their passing, a righteous traveler has absolutely no reason to bring harm to these harmless creatures."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_scintling.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.4F3B4990BE6C2A4A.title: "Scintling"
	quest.4F5A2E2A5C7F4837.quest_desc: [
		"Acquiring the mythical &aForgotten Ingots&r requires a perilous descent into the dark, crumbling vaults of the Catacomb Structure. "
		""
		"These legendary bars of metal cannot be mined from the earth; they must be plundered directly from the sealed offering chests of the dead or violently wrenched from the shattered core of the monolithic &aForgotten Guardian&r. "
		""
		"Furthermore, anchoring their ancient power to your gear demands a specialized Smithing Template. "
		""
		"This elusive blueprint is a lost art, hidden exclusively within those same ancient chests, waiting for an artisan brave enough to claim it from the tomb."
	]
	quest.4F5A2E2A5C7F4837.title: "&aForgotten&r"
	quest.4FA6BEA4E646B742.quest_desc: ["Before we can start building our reactor, we'll need to smelt some Coal or Charcoal to create &9Graphite Ingots&r.\\n\\nGraphite, coupled with Iron, is one of the main materials when making a Reactor."]
	quest.4FA6BEA4E646B742.title: "Graphite for Casings"
	quest.501C6B7580453410.quest_desc: [
		"The &aFluidizer&r is a customizable multiblock that has a minimum size of 3x3x3. "
		""
		"Just like the other multiblocks, the frame will need to be made out of Casings, while the faces can be made out of Glass."
	]
	quest.505E193E3466871A.quest_desc: [
		"Your next metallurgical milestone requires the acquisition of &cIesnium&r, an exotic ore crucial for forging top-tier ritual components."
		""
		"While conventional processing manuals instruct acolytes to go foraging deep within the subterranean veins of the Nether, this automated workspace allows you to bypass manual mining entirely."
		""
		"To manufacture this mineral, route a line of Ancient Debris directly into the beam path of an Atomic Reconstructor from the Actually Additions mod. The intense, high-energy particle stream will destabilize the debris, reorganizing its molecular density to yield a pure, unrefined sample of &cIesnium&r for your production lines."
	]
	quest.505E193E3466871A.quest_subtitle: "Bypassing Nether mining through high-energy atomic reorganization."
	quest.505E193E3466871A.title: "Transmuting Metamaterials: &cIesnium&r"
	quest.511144EF336BFAF5.quest_desc: [
		"The Smog Spires pierce the heavens as the primary source of the realm's suffocating haze. "
		""
		"Yet, the towers do not choke the skies alone—one cannot overlook the unnatural contributions of the &2Mogs&r and &3S'mogs&r. "
		""
		"Those who dare traverse this blighted landscape will encounter Blisterberries, Coarse Deepsoil, and active Smog Vents. Approach them at your own peril..."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_smogspires.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.511144EF336BFAF5.title: "Smog Spires"
	quest.5128B119DFFF0C4C.quest_desc: [
		"The &3Steam Locomotive&r is the most basic &5Locomotive&r. It can be powered by giving it water, furnance fuel, and waiting. "
		""
		"It'll need constant water to keep working. "
		""
		"Don't worry that just means the smoke coming out of the top of it is Water Vapor, which is safe for the Environment."
		""
		"Well the Coal part isn't the best for the Environment... eh its &2Minecraft&r what do we care!"
	]
	quest.51641B23C6AED9DC.quest_subtitle: "Craft yourself a makeshift parachute out of clouds"
	quest.51641B23C6AED9DC.title: "Parachutes!"
	quest.517977BB9C67C6FC.quest_desc: ["Found in Piglin Bastion treasure chests."]
	quest.517977BB9C67C6FC.quest_subtitle: "Found in Bastion Remnant chests"
	quest.5180CDD196518F64.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Strap Iron Tracks&r, like the &6Abandoned Tracks&r, are perfect for the cheapskates. They go much slower than the other &6tracks&r but no risk of derailment!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_strap.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.51B59619BAB0620F.title: "Find a Twilight Swamp"
	quest.51C59FDF0BD11FDF.quest_desc: [
		"To define a Wigglewood Tree is to look upon total structural unpredictability. "
		""
		"These strange entities grow with a frantic, shifting energy, contorting themselves into bizarre shapes and unpredictable sizes as if trying to break free from the soil. "
		""
		"Their dark brown trunks stand in stark, beautiful contrast to the pale pink leaves that whisper in the wind. "
		""
		"They claim sole dominion over the Wigglewood Forests, though travelers have also reported sightings of their crooked silhouettes stretching deep within the Dense Forests."
	]
	quest.51E2728C5E35A152.quest_desc: [
		"The precious mineral known as &bFroststeel&r is a rare treasure locked exclusively within the unforgiving, frozen biomes of the realm. "
		""
		"It takes root deep inside the treacherous veins of Shiverstone—the slippery, ice-like substrate that completely replaces common Depthrock within the bleak Frostfields and the suffocating Frosty Smogstem Forests, extending its reach into the sub-zero abysses of the Icy Seas. "
		""
		"Excavating this ore is a perilous endeavor, as the Shiverstone floor robs travelers of their traction while inflicting a numbing chill that slightly slows their movements. "
		""
		"Fortunately, a mining pick is not the sole method of acquisition; the ravenous &4Munchers&r frequently devour these crystalline veins, allowing clever hunters to plunder a bounty of raw nuggets directly from the beasts' ruptured bellies."
	]
	quest.51E2728C5E35A152.title: "&bFroststeel&r"
	quest.532229D285CA4858.quest_desc: [
		"To secure an automated influx of materials from the physical manufacturing sector back into the digital archives, an engineer must mount the &9Importer&r interface cable. "
		""
		"This tactical reclamation mechanism actively targets a connected block's physical inventory, systematically draining its contents and pulling those assets directly back into your network storage array. "
		""
		"It serves as a vital component for defensive sustainability, commonly affixed to the undercarriages of processing furnaces to instantly siphon out finished ingots the moment the heat subsides. "
		""
		"To guarantee strict sorting protocol, the unit incorporates an internal indexing registry, allowing a logistics officer to precisely filter which specific item IDs are permitted to enter the main network bus line."
	]
	quest.532229D285CA4858.quest_subtitle: "Section IX: Automated Resource Harvesting"
	quest.532229D285CA4858.title: "&9Input Extraction&r: Centralized Asset Intake"
	quest.53594EBA9F7BA840.quest_desc: ["The Advanced Item Loader is everything the regular one is but can be used from anywhere near the &6Track&r. Next to, above, next to on the other side. Use the &4Crowbar&r to change its direction."]
	quest.53C460B13560066F.quest_desc: [
		"Constructing the pentacle layout for Strigeor's Higher Binding marks your entry into the second tier of &6Infusion Rituals&r. While this advanced atmospheric matrix is capable of driving a diverse array of transmutation loops, your immediate production targets require it to synthesize two critical assets: the Infused Pickaxe and Gray Paste."
		""
		"The Infused Pickaxe serves as a highly specialized harvesting tool capable of shattering dense worldly blocks that normal steel and diamond cannot scratch. Meanwhile, Gray Paste functions as a dense chemical catalyst that you will directly combine with your raw chalk stocks to engineer the next tier of colored modifiers for your expanding ritual facilities."
	]
	quest.53C460B13560066F.quest_subtitle: "Harnessing mid-tier essence for stabilized alloys and enchanted instrumentation."
	quest.53C460B13560066F.title: "Advanced Metamaterial: Strigeor's Higher Binding"
	quest.53EA32CC19AE896C.quest_subtitle: "Open 10 containers"
	quest.53FDC6C536E50A1A.quest_desc: [
		"The gentle shoals of &bGwiblings&r represent some of the few peaceful anomalies navigating the dark undercurrents of the seas."
		""
		"Noticeably smaller than their gargantuan counterparts, the &bGwibs&r, these fragile creatures exhibit standard schooling and swimming behaviors indistinguishable from the common fish of the surface world. "
		""
		"They are completely harmless to travelers, darting rhythmically through the deep waters in a constant, graceful dance for survival."
		""
		""
		"{image:undergarden:item/raw_gwibling width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.53FDC6C536E50A1A.title: "&bGwibling&r"
	quest.541D270451DA4320.quest_desc: ["The Switch Track will be needed for moving lanes between the different Special &6Tracks&r. The Arrows on it show which goes where."]
	quest.54468ED84F34EEFE.quest_desc: [
		"Manufacturing your next tier of runic modifiers requires you to harvest high-density organic compounds from extra-dimensional shock troops. You must initiate &6Abras' Open Commanding Conjure&r to force a wave of Demon Possessed Zombified Piglins to cross into the material plane."
		""
		"Prepare your weaponry for a high-intensity combat engagement. Upon terminating these corrupted nether-born entities, you can collect their dropped Demonic Meat. This highly unstable, tissue-based byproduct acts as a potent binding agent; combine it directly with your base chalk stocks in a crafting grid to complete the synthesis of your Pink Chalk modifiers."
	]
	quest.54468ED84F34EEFE.quest_subtitle: "Extracting corrupted tissue samples via spatial command matrices."
	quest.54468ED84F34EEFE.title: "Abyssal Tissues: Pink Chalk"
	quest.54E1E84080816F13.quest_desc: ["Welcome to &6&lForbidden \\& Arcanus&r! \\n\\nTo start this Mod we'll need some Arcane Crystals. Go sieve some Dust."]
	quest.54E1E84080816F13.title: "&6&lForbidden \\& Arcanus"
	quest.54F2CB52D3A7BA87.quest_desc: ["The Item Unloader is the opposite of the Item Loader. It will take items from the &7Carts&r. This one must also be above the &6Track&r."]
	quest.555AA7172905288B.title: "Slay a Lich"
	quest.55D7CD0FA8F1AE48.quest_desc: ["The reason we're all here, &5Trains&r. The mod is called &l&7RailCraft&r don't act surprised. \\n\\nThere's 2 different main &5Trains&r and 1 special mining &5Train&r. \\n\\nThese &5Trains&r all by themselves can get a little boring, so why not attach &7Carts&r to them! Connecting &7Carts&r with &7Carts&r and with &5Trains&r is called Coupling, and to unconnect them is to Decouple. To Couple &5Trains&r and &7Carts&r use a &4Crowbar&r or a &6Track&r with the Coupling &cTrack Kit&r."]
	quest.55DCA040C84DCEF3.quest_desc: [
		"If you want to get your hands on the product the &aFluidizer&r makes, you'll need an &aOutput Port&r on one of the faces."
		""
		"The &aFluidizer&r will need power to operate, so a &cPower Port&r is required to complete the structure."
	]
	quest.56208AC5F5672FC3.quest_desc: [
		"While the baseline satchel significantly reduces field inventory clutter, its mechanical placement cycle introduces noticeable construction downtime as your production lines expand. Achieving complete spatial efficiency requires channeling the stabilization field of the &cSevira's Permanent Confinement&r matrix to manufacture an upgraded Artisanal Ritual Satchel."
		""
		"This advanced apparatus functions nearly identically to its lower-tier counterpart, but features an overhauled deployment engine. Upon right-clicking a holographic guidebook blueprint, the satchel instantly manifests and snaps every required rune, candle, and structural anchor into the world simultaneously, eliminating all construction lag."
		""
		"Furthermore, the artisanal model integrates a specialized reclamation sequence. Right-clicking your central Golden Sacrificial Bowl with the satchel will instantly wipe all active chalk runes from the floor grid while simultaneously vacuuming all peripheral decorations—such as skulls, candles, and crystals—directly back into the bag's internal storage matrix."
		""
		"&o(Note: While this rapid teardown mechanism perfectly automates your room cleanup, it operates strictly as a logistical retrieval tool; the breakdown process does not restore or recharge the physical durability of the chalk items spent during deployment.)&r"
	]
	quest.56208AC5F5672FC3.quest_subtitle: "Maximizing geometric deployment speeds and automated breakdown routines."
	quest.56208AC5F5672FC3.title: "Instant Logistics: Artisanal Satchels"
	quest.564E530B7D181364.quest_subtitle: "Many challenges and just as much loot is waiting for the brave explorer"
	quest.564E530B7D181364.title: "Discover the Ancient Temple of the Valkyries!"
	quest.5737623C55009253.quest_desc: [
		"Synthesized within the maximum-tier field of &9Uphyxes' Inverted Tower&r, the &bIesnium Anvil&r serves as the ultimate pinnacle of equipment maintenance and modification technology. This mechanical powerhouse completely overhauls standard blacksmithing parameters, offering extensive logistical advantages:"
		""
		"&o&nAbsolute Indestructibility&r: The anvil possesses a completely flawless structural integrity matrix. It experiences zero degradation or wear, remaining permanently functional regardless of usage volume."
		""
		"&o&nBypassing Enchantment Thresholds&r: The device forces modification limits upward. Combining identical max-tier items or books will compress the enchantments past standard vanilla boundaries, increasing the cap by an additional tier."
		""
		"&o&nDrastic Experience Compression&r: Total energy expenditure is halved. The workstation cuts your physical experience point requirements precisely in two, rounding down to ensure high-efficiency throughput during complex merges."
		""
		"&o&nDiminished Work Penalties&r: Successive operations on the same item matrix scale much more gracefully, drastically slowing the rapid cost multiplication penalty that plagues lower-tier anvils."
		""
		"&o&nEliminating Budget Blocks&r: The network ceiling is expanded. This mechanics override significantly raises the maximum experience cap, allowing you to finalize heavy, multi-enchanted gear pieces that would normally be rejected as \"Too Expensive!\""
	]
	quest.5737623C55009253.quest_subtitle: "Bypassing standard mechanics to achieve hyper-optimized gear modification."
	quest.5737623C55009253.title: "Unbreaking Synthesis: The &bIesnium Anvil&r"
	quest.579A707576F931C8.quest_desc: ["Eat 115 pieces of Experiment 115. But why stop there? Why ever stop?"]
	quest.580148D1141446A6.quest_desc: [
		"&c&lNether&r too scary for you? Then, you can look for Souls in the &2&lOverworld&r!\\n\\nWithin your World (I made you go to Dark Forests because old &l&6Forbidden \\& Arcanus&r used to have Blocks there) you might find some Lost Souls wandering around.\\n\\nYou can kill them for the Souls that they drop! It is much less efficient though...\\n"
		"If you are having troubles finding Souls, you might wanna look into Soul Looting enchantment on your sword. Killing mobs with this enchantment will occassionally spawn Souls."
	]
	quest.580148D1141446A6.title: "Lost Souls"
	quest.5820EDEF71340A1A.quest_desc: [
		"&6Abandoned Tracks&r are good for the cheapskates and aesthetic. They can be used to bridge accross a few blocks without support. They can only be 2 blocks away from blocks going the same direction, or one block from the opposite direction. They come at the risk of derailment though, basically your &7Cart&r will be thrown off the &6rails&r."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_abandoned.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.58C2ABED43B2EA61.quest_desc: ["&9Model Frameworks&r are the starting point for creating Data Models.\\n\\nTo start collecting data on a specific mob, you'll want to make one of these then &9right click&r the mob you'd like to gather data on. When done properly, the Model Framework will turn into the Data Model of the mob you clicked on.\\n\\nTo gather data for that mob, place the newly created Data Model inside of a &aDeep Learner&r, then start killing that specific mob with the Deep Learner in your inventory."]
	quest.58C2ABED43B2EA61.title: "&9Modeling Mobs"
	quest.5914D015D8543875.quest_desc: [
		"The &aFluidizer&r can operate in one of 3 modes: Solid to Fluid, Combining 2 Solids into a Fluid, or combining 2 Fluids into a new Fluid. "
		""
		"This all depends on the type of &aInjectors&r you use for the multiblock."
		""
		"For example, if you want to convert &dBlutonium&r into a fluid, you can use 1 &aSolid Injector&r."
		""
		"If you want to combine two solids together into something new, you'll build the multiblock with 2 &aSolid Injectors&r."
		""
		"If you want to combine two fluids, you'll use 2 &9Fluid Injectors&r."
		""
		"This might seem confusing, but is important for progression. For example, you'll want to convert Magentite into a fluid in the Fluidizer first, then send it to a &aReprocessor&r with Ludicrite to create Ridiculite."
	]
	quest.59F5ED931FD70C55.quest_desc: [
		"To transition an outpost from manual workbench labor to absolute industrial autonomy, a master engineer must establish a centralized schematic archive. "
		""
		"This automated revolution relies entirely on the manufacture of &9Patterns&r, universally recognized as the literal bread and butter of the autocrafting hierarchy."
		""
		"These specialized data-slate matrices do not hold physical materials; instead, they permanently store precise assembly recipes and processing instructions within their circuits."
		""
		"By logging these encoded matrices into your terminal machinery, you allow the central network to interpret complex blueprints and independently craft advanced items on demand, transforming a primitive fortress into a self-sustaining manufacturing powerhouse."
	]
	quest.59F5ED931FD70C55.quest_subtitle: "Section XXI: The Foundation of Network Autocrafting"
	quest.59F5ED931FD70C55.title: "Schematic Registry: Automated Manufacturing Blueprints"
	quest.5A615BB74A5CD332.quest_desc: [
		"Using the &aReprocessor&r, we can combine everything we've made so far to make a few new ingots."
		""
		"Note: You might need a &9Fluidizer&r to complete this step!"
	]
	quest.5A79137D9EA9EFC0.quest_desc: [
		"Managing mass-resource generation lines demands a sophisticated logistical backbone. If you have not yet established a digitized inventory network, anchoring your logistics to a &dDimensional Storage&r network is highly recommended."
		""
		"To initialize this system, you must construct and place a &dDimensional Storage Actuator&r. This device serves as the core master anchor for your pocket dimension. The block retains its internal memory layout when broken, allowing you to relocate the entire physical block without losing any of your stored commodities."
		""
		"By default, the matrix provides 128 unique inventory slots, with each slot capable of compressing and holding up to 16 full stacks of a single item. However, note that items containing unique &5NBT&r data are completely incompatible with this compression logic. Tools, armor, and modified components will not stack and will consume an entire slot by themselves, making it vital to filter these items out of your automated input pipelines."
	]
	quest.5A79137D9EA9EFC0.title: "The Planar Matrix: &dDimensional Storage&r"
	quest.5AC42BFB6EFAF258.quest_subtitle: "Craft yourself an altar, a multifunctional enchanting and repairing device"
	quest.5AC42BFB6EFAF258.title: "Altar to whom?"
	quest.5ACCF56D41A5CC27.quest_desc: [
		"In order to find the dungeon, the player must throw one of the Eyes which will fly for a few blocks in the direction of the nearest End Gate before dropping to the ground. By default, the eyes have a 10% chance to shatter upon being thrown. "
		""
		"The dungeon is procedurally generated, which means that it doesn't have a particular layout. However, the dungeon has 9 different puzzles and a portal room. Before accessing the End Gate, the player must complete 3 puzzles. "
		""
		"The Portal Room is located right after the final puzzle. In order to activate the portal, you need to find 11 eyes and to craft the powered core. "
	]
	quest.5ACCF56D41A5CC27.title: "Use 12 eyes to visit the End"
	quest.5AD80D3242DD3F60.quest_desc: ["One of the hardest materials to get in the mod!"]
	quest.5AE0DA6972811771.quest_desc: [
		"Securing the complete spectrum of alchemical chalks demands that you manifest and terminate an unyielding, hostile &cAfrit&r entity."
		""
		"While this ceremony is officially categorized under the summoning tree rather than a true &5Possession Ritual&r, the unique chemical nature of this fire spirit still demands a live biological anchor to bridge the dimensional gap. For this particular circle, you must secure a standard overworld cow to serve as the structural sacrifice."
		""
		"Ensure your combat arena is heavily fortified and free of flammable materials before proceeding. The moment your target animal enters the center of the runic perimeter and the offering is executed, the matrix will ignite, immediately releasing the violent entity into your world."
	]
	quest.5AE0DA6972811771.quest_subtitle: "Constructing the high-risk thermal core extraction matrix."
	quest.5AE0DA6972811771.title: "Unbound Combustion: The &cAfrit&r Manifestation"
	quest.5B4B5C148D63ACA1.quest_desc: [
		"The enigmatic constructs known as &aForgotten Minions&r do not belong to the natural order of birth and decay; they are entities born entirely of deliberate creation. "
		""
		"To breathe life into one, an artisan must align a Carved Gloomgourd atop a solid &aBlock of Forgotten Ingots&r, triggering a sudden, silent awakening. "
		""
		"These metallic guardians mirror the defensive behaviors of snow constructs from distant worlds, maintaining absolute loyalty to their creators while relentlessly hurling projectiles at hostile entities. "
		""
		"Possessing a resilient vitality equivalent to twenty standard measures of health, they yield absolutely no earthly remains upon destruction—though only a truly hollow soul would ever raise a blade against them."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_minion.png width:125 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.5B4B5C148D63ACA1.title: "&aForgotten Minions&r"
	quest.5BB6B74BA3AE18D7.quest_desc: [
		"The final bottleneck of automated possession loops is the physical requirement of manually gathering and executing livestock over your runic arrays. To achieve complete hands-free automation, Ars Occultas provides a highly specialized logistical component: the Sacrificial Altar."
		""
		"This device must be installed directly beneath your central Golden Sacrificial Bowl. When powered, the altar completely replaces the requirement for live entity execution by converting raw, liquid magic into a viable biological catalyst."
		""
		"To calibrate this automated matrix, you must place an active Ars Nouveau Source Jar within proximity to supply the necessary fluid energy. Additionally, a Containment Jar holding a trapped specimen of your target sacrifice must be positioned adjacent to the setup. The altar will continuously scan the contained entity's biological frequency, consume a portion of your stored Source fluid, and flawlessly simulate the required sacrifice to initiate your automated possession cycles indefinitely."
	]
	quest.5BB6B74BA3AE18D7.quest_subtitle: "Substituting living biological sacrifices with fluid source energy networks."
	quest.5BB6B74BA3AE18D7.title: "Automated Execution: The Sacrificial Altar"
	quest.5BDADF6C889BB9D1.quest_desc: [
		"Manufacturing your next tier of runic modifiers requires you to harness the high-throughput crushing capabilities of your mid-to-high-tier processing thralls. Both the &9Fatma's Incentivized Attraction&r matrix (for the &9Marid Crusher&r) and the &aOphyx' Calling&r matrix (for the &aDjinni Crusher&r) possess the necessary structural dampening fields to run this specialized extraction line."
		""
		"To acquire the required components, route raw quantities of Ice, Packed Ice, or Blue Ice directly into your active spirit’s processing area. These advanced entities will rapidly fracture the frozen compounds into localized, ultra-cold crushed fragments without generating the ambient friction heat that would otherwise liquefy the materials into waste water."
		""
		"Once harvested, take these stabilized sub-zero dusts straight to your crafting grid and combine them with your base chalk stocks to finalize the synthesis of your Light Blue Chalk modifiers."
	]
	quest.5BDADF6C889BB9D1.quest_subtitle: "Processing high-density ice aggregates into advanced colored modifiers."
	quest.5BDADF6C889BB9D1.title: "Thermal Extraction: Light Blue Chalk"
	quest.5C776EA056A14C57.quest_desc: [
		"Before you can begin shackling entities to your automated factory lines, you must manufacture the fundamental medium of all occult geometry: &aChalk&r."
		""
		"Advanced blueprints demand multiple colors of chalk to complete their intricate grids. To begin your arcane progression, &bWhite Chalk&r serves as the base layer."
		""
		"Your first step requires smelting Otherstone within a standard furnace to produce burnt variants, alongside throwing raw Otherworld Logs into the cleansing flames of a &dSpiritfire&r matrix. Combining these resulting components allows you to forge Impure White Chalk."
		""
		"To refine the medium, toss the impure chalk directly back into the &dSpiritfire&r to cleanse it of earthly impurities. Left-clicking the ground with your purified tool will transcribe the required &mdemonic&r runic glyphs into the world. Because these etched symbols are notoriously tedious to scrub away by hand, it is highly recommended to craft a specialized &aChalk Brush&r to easily wipe the floor clean when re-configuring your ritual rooms."
	]
	quest.5C776EA056A14C57.title: "Preparing for a Ritual: &eChalk"
	quest.5D1F4B6E9CED99E7.quest_desc: ["Once you have located a swamp, go the the centre and you will find a mostly buried maze containing the Minoshroom boss."]
	quest.5D1F4B6E9CED99E7.title: "Slay a Minoshroom"
	quest.5D229FA3A5F92954.quest_desc: [
		"While the bloodthirsty beasts known as &4Munchers&r share the same relentless aggression as other hostile horrors haunting the &2&lUndergarden&r, their unique biological dietary habits make them an incredibly valuable target for resource gatherers. "
		""
		"These ravenous creatures constantly feast upon the raw veins of the earth, storing unrefined minerals directly within their heavy gullets. "
		""
		"Should you successfully cut them down, their ruptured bellies can surrender a precious harvest of refined &7Cloggrum&r and shimmering &bFroststeel Nuggets&r—making them a dangerous but highly lucrative source of metallurgy for those daring enough to hunt them."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_muncher.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.5D229FA3A5F92954.title: "&4Muncher&r"
	quest.5D5C73EE97599674.quest_desc: [
		"To dictate exactly which extra-dimensional entity you pull across the veil, you must craft a designated &bBook of Binding&r tailored to that tier of spirit."
		""
		"The process requires casting standard black dye into the cleansing flames of a &dSpiritfire&r matrix to yield Purified Ink. Using this specialized pigment, you can construct your first Book of Binding to securely shackle a lesser &aFoliot&r class entity to your bidding."
		""
		"Alternatively, you may craft an Empty Book of Binding. This blank ledger serves as a generic template that can be dyed at a later date to match whatever ritual tier your factory demands."
		""
		"To finalize the attunement, ensure you have your target entity's specific page material ready. Fulfilling the ritual without a properly matching ledger will cause the summoning matrix to destabilize, wasting your hard-earned chalk charges and sacrificial materials."
	]
	quest.5D5C73EE97599674.title: "&bBooks of &dBinding"
	quest.5D7B2EFAB7E59856.quest_desc: ["Throw a diamond into a 2x2 pool of water surrounded by poppies/dandelions"]
	quest.5DDF74E99C83CE60.quest_desc: [
		"Weaponizing your access to &cIesnium&r unlocks the pinnacle of automated resource generation. By establishing a direct link to the spatial pockets of the Otherworld, you can legally shackle a dedicated workforce to a lifetime of subterranean labor on your behalf."
		""
		"To initialize this extraction line, you must construct a &dDimensional Mineshaft&r terminal. This apparatus acts as a doorway to raw mineral deposits. To power the system, you must trap a specialized Mining Demon inside a soul lamp and insert the vessel directly into the terminal's input matrix. While any tier of mining spirit will validate this quest, scaling up to advanced, higher-tier entities will drastically increase mining speeds and heavily multiply the drop rates of rare ores like Iesnium."
		""
		"Note that the mineshaft terminal features a primitive logistical interface and lacks any internal auto-export capabilities. You must manually extract the incoming ore yields using baseline hoppers, specialized logistics piping, or dedicated Transporting Demons. Ensure your extraction pipelines possess high throughput; if the internal buffer storage fills to capacity, the terminal will instantly void any incoming materials over the limit."
	]
	quest.5DDF74E99C83CE60.quest_subtitle: "Constructing automated resource mining nodes across the spatial veil."
	quest.5DDF74E99C83CE60.title: "Sub-Planar Extraction: &dDimensional Mineshafts&r"
	quest.5E63C78CDC44FF95.quest_desc: [
		"In their raw, unrefined form, Rotten Blisterberries possess a highly unstable structure that prevents them from being launched or thrown by hand without premature rupture. "
		""
		"However, when sealed and bound into tactical Blisterbombs, their structural integrity is secured, transforming them into a highly effective thrown ordnance. "
		""
		"For siege-level devastation, an artisan can advance this chemical engineering to construct Boomgourds. "
		""
		"This heavy explosive behaves identically to traditional surface-world TNT upon ignition, but introduces a catastrophic secondary effect: the blast wall shatters to violently scatter burning Blisterberry shrapnel across a massive radius, choking the battlefield in a rain of corrosive rot."
	]
	quest.5E63C78CDC44FF95.title: "Explosives!!!"
	quest.5E750DB2244A67A1.quest_desc: [
		"The &6Turnout track&r is the first from hitting a &6track&r with a Spike Maul. It can help go two directions, forward and to a side. It can be switched with a Switch next to the &6track&r."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_turnout.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.5ED35874D59A7595.quest_desc: [
		"Neutralizing the threat summoned via &4Tibira's Attraction&r allows you to harvest the ultimate tier of colored runic materials. Securing the &9Marid Essence&r dropped from the remains of that entity provides the exact sub-spatial catalyst required for your final chalk upgrades."
		""
		"Take this volatile essence directly to your crafting grid and bond it with your remaining base chalk stocks. The elemental core will permanently realign the medium, allowing you to finalize the manufacture of your Blue Chalk modifiers. This completes the full spectrum of available colored inks, granting your facility the precise programmatic tools needed to layout the most advanced automated factory pentacles in the pack."
	]
	quest.5ED35874D59A7595.quest_subtitle: "Refining premier elemental remnants into top-tier runic modifiers."
	quest.5ED35874D59A7595.title: "High-Density Distillation: Blue Chalk"
	quest.5FCA6F5FE97780B7.quest_desc: [
		"Though they possess a distinct, animalistic presence, &eGronglets&r are technically unique vegetative growths rather than living creatures. "
		""
		"These fascinating entities grow exclusively along the bark of the colossal Grongle Trees, anchoring themselves to the timber as fixed landmarks of the canopy. "
		""
		"Once mature, they continuously bleed a comforting, ambient noise and a soft, rhythmic light into the surrounding wilderness. "
		""
		"They remain highly coveted by architects and travelers alike, serving as the ultimate organic decoration for those seeking to bring the warmth of the jungle indoors."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_gronglet.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.5FCA6F5FE97780B7.title: "&eGronglets&r"
	quest.60244F26B9ABED49.title: "&a1024B Fluid Storage Part"
	quest.6092490EC9008A05.quest_desc: [
		"To secure an automated harvest of raw elements without manual mining, an engineer must install the specialized &4Destructor&r interface. "
		""
		"This tactical demolition mechanism actively targets the physical block space directly adjacent to its excavation face, systematically shattering the material and pulling those assets directly back into your network storage array. "
		""
		"It serves as a vital component for industrial sustainability, commonly paired with a matter-generating Constructor to instantly clear and process raw timber or stone the moment it reaches maturity. "
		""
		"To guarantee a precise sorting protocol, the unit incorporates an internal whitelist registry, enabling a logistics officer to filter which specific block IDs are permitted to be broken, preventing accidental destruction of structural base components."
	]
	quest.6092490EC9008A05.quest_subtitle: "Section XI: Physical World Demolition Interfaces"
	quest.6092490EC9008A05.title: "&4Reclamation Terminal&r: Automated Deconstruction"
	quest.609CA1ACFA981BD5.quest_desc: ["The &cRouting Kit&r is used with the passing tickets."]
	quest.6124C0E9E419694B.quest_desc: [
		"When a craftsman melds common &7Cloggrum&r implements with rare &aForgotten Ingots&r via a sacred Smithing Template, the resulting armaments transcend standard smithing boundaries. "
		""
		"These stand undisputed as the pinnacle of tools within the realm, forged with an innate, structural efficiency attuned specifically to dismantle the dense stone and flora of the &2&lUndergarden&r. "
		""
		"When drawn in anger, the blades and axes channel a primeval malice, delivering devastating, heightened damage to almost every native entity stalking the dark. "
		""
		"Only the colossal &aForgotten Guardian&r—sharing the weapon's own metallic bloodline—and the ancient, corrupted &cRot Beast&r possess the unique resilience required to shrug off this absolute lethality."
	]
	quest.6124C0E9E419694B.title: "&aForgotten&r Tools"
	quest.6148DA91475AF128.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.61A4D6C2B0B4786D.quest_desc: ["Find a stronghold in the Dark Forest biome, then place a boss trophy on the pedestal to access it. Then locate the room with the Knight Phantoms."]
	quest.61A4D6C2B0B4786D.title: "Slay the 6 Knight Phantoms"
	quest.61C93ABE07742DCD.quest_desc: [
		"The Steam Turbine uses Steam to make FE and EU energy. \\n\\nIt's 3x2x2 building of only Steam Turbine Housing, and it'll need a Turbine Motor in it, and Steam piped in."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_turbine.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.6224E46C00B69F5D.quest_desc: ["Find the Mazebreaker pickaxe in the secret labyrinth vault."]
	quest.632BFEC0E8AF7126.quest_desc: ["Have a full block of Experiment 115 with Redstone sprinkles."]
	quest.632BFEC0E8AF7126.title: "Making a note: Huge Success!"
	quest.647A87E800C703C3.quest_desc: [
		"The Green Jungle stands as a breathtaking spectacle within the realm. "
		""
		"It is a colossal, untamed paradise dominated by massive, towering Gronglegrowth Trees that stretch high into the canopy. "
		""
		"If you dare to look up into their ancient branches, you might just spot the elusive &eGronglets&r clinging to the bark."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_grongle.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.647A87E800C703C3.title: "Gronglegrowth"
	quest.64A6C2A397051CFA.quest_desc: [
		"The gateway to this mod begins with the &9Summoning Ritual&r. These dark ceremonies allow you to pull helpful extra-dimensional entities across the veil, securing loyal thralls to automate your resource crushing, smelting, and advanced processing as your power grows."
		""
		"Your initial target is a &aFoliot Crusher&r. This lesser spirit will serve as your automated ore pulverizer, generating the specific crushed dusts required to forge higher-tier ritual chalks."
		""
		"To begin, drop your Unbound Book and your &aDictionary of Spirits&r into any crafting grid. This process binds a native entity to the pages, preparing the vessel required for the upcoming ritual."
		""
		"Next, consult your &aDictionary of Spirits&r directly. Navigate to the &dPentacles&r tab on the left sidebar and select the blueprint for &bAviar's Circle&r. If the schematic is hidden, browse through the introductory lore pages or click \"Mark All As Read\" to instantly unlock the full catalog of blueprints."
		""
		"This specific geometric pattern is the key to summoning your new minion. While viewing the blueprint, click the eye icon in the bottom-left corner of the page to project a holographic overlay directly into the world, guiding your block placement."
		""
		"After constructing the foundation, place at least 4 Sacrificial Bowls anywhere within an 8-block horizontal radius of your central Golden Sacrificial Bowl. Deposit the required catalysts into the standard bowls, then right-click the central Golden Bowl with your Bound Book to ignite the summoning circle."
		""
		"This is what it should look like before you acttually start the ritual."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/aviarcircle.png width:200 height:200 align:center}"
	]
	quest.64A6C2A397051CFA.quest_subtitle: "Aviar's Circle"
	quest.64A6C2A397051CFA.title: "&bFirst &dRitual"
	quest.64C105E1E2F97900.quest_desc: ["The Spike Mauls are used on normal &6Tracks&r to switch their modes. Very helpful for trying to make intersections!"]
	quest.64C105E1E2F97900.title: "Smart Switch"
	quest.64D73FF43C7D5AB9.quest_desc: ["Go back to the Troll Cave, locate the large obsidian vault and mine inside with the giant pickaxe to obtain the Lamp of Cinders."]
	quest.64E85274D24FE394.quest_desc: [
		"To maintain immediate, visual command over a facility's skyrocketing material counts without constantly referencing a terminal screen, an engineer must affix the &9Storage Monitor&r to the structure's walls. "
		""
		"Once this specialized display panel is securely linked to the primary digital network bus line, it functions as a real-time ledger for a single, designated resource. "
		""
		"The monitor projects a shifting, localized data field directly onto its face, constantly reflecting the precise, up-to-the-millisecond quantity of that specific item ID currently hoarded within the central digital storage cells."
		""
		"It stands as an invaluable tool for logistics officers needing to track vital ingot reserves or ammunition stockpiles during active defensive operations."
	]
	quest.64E85274D24FE394.title: "&9Visual Monitoring&r: Direct Count Display"
	quest.65C8A43FEDBA3835.quest_desc: [
		"To encode a master schematic archive into the central database, an engineer must interface with the &3Pattern Grid&r. "
		""
		"This specialized terminal acts as a tactical imprinting press, allowing a technician to permanently burn complex assembly recipes onto blank Patterns for network integration."
		""
		"&n&oSchematic Injection&r&r: The most efficient method to map a blueprint involves referencing the core Just Enough Items index, executing a swift override command via the tracking interface to automatically align the required components within the primary grid."
		""
		"&o&nEncoding Protocol&r&r: The upper receptacle on the right-hand panel is engineered specifically to warehouse raw, blank Patterns. With a blank template securely slotted into the matrix, the operator must press the directional Arrow mechanism directly below to trigger a high-frequency imprint, locking the assembly instructions into the chip's circuits."
		""
		"Once the data matrix is finalized, the technician must retrieve the encoded Pattern and secure it within a designated network Autocrafter to initialize automated assembly routines."
	]
	quest.65C8A43FEDBA3835.quest_subtitle: "Section XXII: The Recipe Encoding Matrix"
	quest.65C8A43FEDBA3835.title: "Blueprint Imprinter: Programming Schematic Strata"
	quest.662922793C0ED6E0.quest_desc: ["Obtain all different wood, leaf, or natural block and their variants from the Twilight Forest mod!"]
	quest.662922793C0ED6E0.title: "Maniacal Dendrologist"
	quest.66D85424EC74EDCC.quest_desc: [
		"When a scout or frontline vanguard advances far beyond the signal range of the primary colony fortress, they can no longer draw assets from the central hub. "
		""
		"To preserve logistical supremacy in untamed territories, an engineer must construct the &9Portable Grid&r."
		""
		"This compact device functions as an entirely independent, localized storage manifold that operates without a direct connection to a network framework."
		""
		"By inserting a standalone media cell directly into its integrated terminal slot, a traveler can seamlessly interface with, search, and extract materials from a single &9Storage Disk&r while completely isolated in the field, carrying a virtual armory directly upon their person."
	]
	quest.66D85424EC74EDCC.quest_subtitle: "Section XIX: The Off-Grid Portable Interface"
	quest.66D85424EC74EDCC.title: "Field Equipment: Isolated Storage Manifolds"
	quest.6751F2651063B3A5.quest_desc: [
		"To encounter a Blood Mushroom is to witness a grotesque anomaly of the lowlands. "
		""
		"These gargantuan fungi grow with heavy, branching crowns, spreading wide to block out the twilight sky. "
		""
		"Their trunks and caps are predominantly bone-white, but the stark coloration is marred by localized, bleeding capillaries. "
		""
		"These stark crimson patches seep into the pale fibers, giving the unsettling illusion that the landscape itself is bleeding."
	]
	quest.677C5D35DADA4A42.quest_desc: ["&cThe Coupler&r is for connecting or disconnecting &7Carts&r. Coupling is the phrase for connecting &7Carts&r. \\n\\nIt can be configured with a &4Crowbar&r to couple, decouple, or auto couple. Needs Redstone to work."]
	quest.67A2347534269528.quest_desc: [
		"The vile entities known as &9Sploogies&r emerge only rarely from the dark recesses of the earth, yet their presence is an immediate curse to any traveler. "
		""
		"They maintain a cowardly, parasitic strategy—firing streams of caustic, pressurized spit from a distance while emitting wet, deeply repulsive sucking sounds that echo through the caverns. "
		""
		"Despite their sudden aggression, they possess no true courage; a single retaliatory strike will shatter their nerve, causing them to turn and flee in a panicked scramble reminiscent of a startled baby piglin. "
		""
		"Upon their demise, their fluid-bloated bodies burst to leave behind nothing of worth save for a few common Depthrock Pebbles."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_sploogie.png width:125 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.67A2347534269528.title: "&9Sploogie&r"
	quest.67AFCBCE7AAC3089.quest_desc: [
		"To get a Turbine spinning, we'll need these &crequired&r components:"
		""
		"- &9Rotor Bearings&r are placed at one end of the shaft of the turbine. This can be on any face, but dictates where the shaft extrude from. This is typically placed in the center of the bottom face."
		""
		"- &eRotor Shafts&r extend from one Rotor Bearing to the opposite side of the turbine, all the way to a single Turbine Housing block, creating the shaft for the Turbine."
		""
		"- &9Rotor Blades&r make the rotor spin. These are placed onto the Rotor Shafts and can be multiple blocks in length. Each Blade can handle a certain amount of vapor, and determines how many are needed based on your reactor's production rates."
		""
		"Here is an example of a Vertical Shaft setup for a Turbine, with the Turbine Coil of Lead on the top."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/maxbasicturbine.png width:150 height:150 align:center}"
	]
	quest.67AFCBCE7AAC3089.title: "Turbine Shaft"
	quest.67F454DF06908583.quest_subtitle: "You should try feeding this to animals"
	quest.67F454DF06908583.title: "Purple Shooty Plant"
	quest.681FB9758B02412D.quest_desc: [
		"Utilizing &dSpiritfire&r allows you to bypass manual exploration by directly transmuting mundane overworld resources into their ethereal counterparts. While you can harvest these items naturally in the wild under the sensory influence of the &bThird Eye&r, utilizing the flame matrix provides a much more direct, automatable path for your early logistics."
		""
		"Tossing standard &bAndesite&r into the flames converts it into &3Otherstone&r, an inorganic material that serves as a permanent, non-consuming hearth block when ignited with &dSpiritfire&r."
		""
		"Casting an &aOak Sapling&r into the matrix yields an Otherworld variant. Once planted and matured, this tree appears identical to standard oak to the untrained eye. However, breaking its bark while under the active status effects of the &bThird Eye&r allows you to harvest its true form."
		""
		"&o(Note: If the harvested wood accidentally reverts to standard oak logs, a known physical limitation requires you to harvest the tree's canopy from the top downward to secure the drop.)&r"
		""
		"Finally, dropping pristine &eDiamonds&r into the pyre converts them into &dSpirit Attuned Gems&r, a vital structural component for almost every advanced mechanism and ritual foundation in your upcoming progression."
	]
	quest.681FB9758B02412D.title: "Holy &dSpiritfire&r Batman!!"
	quest.68640EC6825C9746.quest_subtitle: "Tools made of this diamond level equivalent of the skies have an odd effect when  used on other blocks"
	quest.68640EC6825C9746.title: "This is not Diamond!"
	quest.68741956F948EAE3.quest_desc: ["It appears as though nature has adjusted well to this new climate, pigs and cows grew wings, sheep can float thru the skies. This berry bush seems to be a major source of food."]
	quest.68741956F948EAE3.quest_subtitle: "Flora and Fauna"
	quest.6898798869C573DD.quest_desc: [
		"Terminating the hostile Goat of Mercy materialized from the containment field of &9Xeovrenth Adjure&r allows your facility to harvest a critical late-game catalyst. Securing the Cruelty Essence dropped from the remains of this entity provides the dense, volatile spiritual profile necessary to stabilize your final chalk upgrades."
		""
		"Take this concentrated essence straight to a standard crafting grid and combine it with raw Cocoa Beans. The organic plant matter will bind and temper the intense energy of the essence, permanently altering the compound to finalize the synthesis of your Brown Chalk modifiers. This locks in one of the final required keys needed to program your absolute highest tiers of automated multi-block factories."
	]
	quest.6898798869C573DD.quest_subtitle: "Processing concentrated vital essences into high-tier runic modifiers."
	quest.6898798869C573DD.title: "Abyssal Refining: Brown Chalk"
	quest.6904EC449FBEE387.quest_desc: [
		"While a novice technician can rely on direct proximity—placing physical mechanisms side-by-side to draw power from the primary hub—such dense arrangements rapidly fail as a colony's infrastructure grows."
		""
		"To bridge the architectural void and weave an expansive logistics grid, an engineer must manufacture specialized &9Cables&r."
		""
		"These insulated conduits function as the literal nervous system of the facility, carrying the digital life pulse across vast chambers. "
		""
		"They allow individual terminals, drives, and specialized bays to be positioned at strategic defensive intervals rather than crammed against the core, standing as an mandatory, foundational staple for any high-tier resource network."
	]
	quest.6904EC449FBEE387.quest_subtitle: "Section V: Spatial Expansion and Component Linking"
	quest.6904EC449FBEE387.title: "STRUCTURAL CONDUIT: REINFORCED DATA WIRING"
	quest.6918F58588CE9115.quest_desc: ["Reach the top of the massive tower and slay the Ur Ghast. Killing Carminite Ghastlings near the Ghast Traps, then powering the trap when the Ur Ghast is near will do heavy damage to it."]
	quest.6918F58588CE9115.title: "Slay the Ur Ghast"
	quest.69642A3618E86DED.quest_desc: [
		"To build the frame for the &aReprocessor&r, you'll need a lot of Casings. This also means a lot of Cyanite."
		""
		"Start by building a hollow 3 block wide, 3 block deep, and 7 block tall structure. This is the frame."
		""
		"If done right, you'll have an empty spot in the middle of the bottom and top face. "
		""
		"For the vertical faces, you can either use &aReprocessor Glass&r or one of the required &aReprocessor&r parts like the Power Port, Controller, etc."
		""
		"If you'd like to see an image of what the frame will look like, check the images below!"
		""
		"The frame of the Reprocessor multiblock:"
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/reprocessorframe.png width:150 height:175 align:center}"
		""
		""
		"A fully built Reprocessor:"
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/reprocessorfull.png width:150 height:150 align:center}"
	]
	quest.69642A3618E86DED.title: "The Frame"
	quest.6ADDFD55AD0DF7D4.quest_desc: [
		"Combining &9Ridiculite Ingots&r with &cRossinite&r in a &aReprocessor&r will create &dInanite Ingots&r."
		""
		"We can now use these to make a block of &dInanite&r."
	]
	quest.6B04FC81351CD1AB.quest_desc: [
		"To project the advanced data streams of an empire's central database directly into the field, an operative must establish a high-frequency atmospheric relay."
		""
		"This tactical mobilization sequence initializes with the fabrication of the &3Wireless Transmitter&r."
		""
		"Engineers can seamlessly append this broadcasting node to any structural coordinate along the active network bus line, requiring no specialized terminal placement to spark its array."
		""
		"Once supplied with system data, it radiates a powerful, localized energy field across the frontier—standing as the mandatory, foundational beacon required to bind mobile &9Wireless Grids&r to the main core, allowing scouts to command the facility's archives from afar."
	]
	quest.6B04FC81351CD1AB.quest_subtitle: "Section XXVI: Remote Network Access Grid Initialization"
	quest.6B04FC81351CD1AB.title: "Wireless Node: Broadband Signal Emission"
	quest.6B3B0F9EE26ABAD3.quest_desc: [
		"Step 6: Forester"
		""
		"If your style is wood, it’s recommended to build a Forester’s Hut next. That way your new Forester can start gathering wood for your next builds and for tools and other items."
	]
	quest.6C14D1B60124C2B2.quest_desc: [
		"The &9Tunnel Bore&r is perfect for automatically placing &6Rails&r especially under mountains or hills. \\n\\nIt'll need 3 things to start working: &9Bore Head&r, fuel like Coal, and &6Rails&r. Once it has all 3 just let it go! \\n\\nRemember to keep track of the items going in it!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_tunnel.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.6C163E005351FF6D.quest_desc: ["The &cWhistle Kit&r when active with Redstone will cause the &5Locomotives&r to set off their whistles."]
	quest.6C4B93FE64BD418D.quest_desc: [
		"Tearing open a passage to the &2&lUndergarden&r requires a ritual heavily reminiscent of the gateway to &c&lThe Nether&r. "
		""
		"A grand, rectangular threshold must be constructed, mirroring the exact height and width of those obsidian gates. "
		""
		"Yet, this realm rejects volcanic glass; its gateway must be forged from the heavy weight of stone, requiring a frame of classic Stone Bricks, weathered Mossy Stone Bricks, or dark Deepslate Bricks. "
		""
		"Once the monolithic arch stands complete, striking its inner hollow with the elusive Catalyst will ignite the veil and open the path."
	]
	quest.6D4FB6291CA8D1A6.quest_desc: [
		"The Smogstem Trees are defined by their thick, bulbous bases, reminiscent of the ancient giants that once braced the surface world. "
		""
		"They bear leaves of a deep sapphire hue and trunks of a muted, ash-grey bark. "
		""
		"These imposing structures possess an adaptive resilience, claiming domain across multiple territories: they anchor the suffocating Smogstem Forests, choke the light from the Dense Forests, and even take root within the damp soil of the Indigo Mushroom Bogs."
	]
	quest.6DB65926EE6D6C2E.quest_desc: ["These &cTracks Kits&r are for changing momentum with your &7Carts&r. \\n\\nThe &cTransition Kits&r change the speed of the passing &5Locomotive&r, needs redstone power. \\nThe &cBooster Kits&r will speed up the &7Cart&r if powered and slow down the &7Cart&r if not powered. \\nThe &cControl Kit&r gives the &7Carts&r a little push, when powered it'll change the direction it pushes it in. \\nThe &cThrottle Kit&r will change the speed of a passing &5Locomotive&r to whatever speed is configured, needs to be powered with redstone. \\nThe &cLauncher Kit&r will quite literally throw your &7Cart&r!"]
	quest.6DB9E297C9248966.quest_desc: [
		"Acquiring &aLime Chalk&r opens the gateway to &5Possession Rituals&r. This discipline introduces a distinct mechanical departure from your previous setups: the matrix cannot draw energy solely from item catalysts and requires a living biological sacrifice to anchor the entity. Early configurations consume minor entities like chickens, bees, or bats, but advanced circles deep in the tech tree will scale up to require massive, high-health organisms."
		""
		"The initiation parameters for these ceremonies are strictly enforced. Even if you have perfectly dressed your peripheral bowls with the required item reagents and deposited your Book of Binding into the central Golden Sacrificial Bowl, the summoning matrix will remain completely inert. To spark the reaction, you must manually execute the captured target directly over the chalk runes."
		""
		"To facilitate this process, it is highly recommended to manufacture a dedicated biological containment unit—such as an Empty Soul Gem, Mob Imprisonment Tool, or Quantum Catcher—to effortlessly transport your sacrificial specimens into the center of your ritual room."
		""
		"The foundational circle for this tree is &eHeidryn's Lure&r, which is utilized primarily to manifest mundane commodities like baseline skeleton skulls and early-game End Stone. Because your factory logistics likely outpaced these low-tier items, you may bypass this initial schematic entirely and advance straight to constructing the second-tier matrix: &aIhagan's Enthrallment&r."
	]
	quest.6DB9E297C9248966.quest_subtitle: "Constructing organic catalysts and manual ignition criteria."
	quest.6DB9E297C9248966.title: "Lethal Anchors: &5Possession Rituals&r"
	quest.6E7C4228CD2B6BB9.quest_desc: [
		"This &4Crowbar&r has a few different modes, each with change the design of a &5Locomotive&r. "
		""
		"From default which is described while hovering over the item in your inventory:"
		""
		"--none which goes to &7grey&r"
		""
		"--&6Halloween&r which makes it spooky"
		""
		"--and &cChristmas&r which makes it festive!"
	]
	quest.6EB945C2C1B04265.quest_subtitle: "In the past, this mythical armor bestowed wings upon the heavenly warriors, only the cape retained a fraction of that ancient power"
	quest.6EB945C2C1B04265.title: "The ultimate armor"
	quest.6F416275B6F6D8F0.quest_desc: [
		"Deep within the choking fumes of the Smog Spires hangs the volatile fruit known as Blisterberries. "
		""
		"Born in such an abrasive, toxic environment, a vast portion of the harvest is rapidly overtaken by a necrotic decay before it can even be plucked. "
		""
		"To consume these blackened, rotten specimens is an act of sheer madness—yet, for the daring alchemist, this very rot holds a different kind of promise, harboring volatile compounds that may prove highly useful in the brewing of potent blights."
	]
	quest.6F4BD1431AB81612.title: "Find a Dark Forest"
	quest.6FA1D1BAD194187D.quest_desc: ["Defeat a Twilight Wraith in a large Hollow Hill."]
	quest.6FA1D1BAD194187D.title: "I See Right Through You"
	quest.6FF8291A3D5763F2.quest_desc: [
		"Upon processing your first yields of &aRaw Iesnium Ore&r, prioritizing your refined ingots toward fabricating an &dIesnium Pickaxe&r is highly advantageous."
		""
		"This advanced mining instrument matches the exact dimensional frequency of your previous Infused Pickaxe, allowing it to easily shatter dense otherworldly minerals like Iesnium ore veins. However, this metallic alloy possesses a significantly superior crystalline structure, meaning it offers a massive upgrade to maximum durability."
		""
		"Upgrading your mining gear to this tier drastically lowers your maintenance downtime, ensuring your extraction tools last significantly longer before needing a restoration ritual cycle."
	]
	quest.6FF8291A3D5763F2.quest_subtitle: "Upgrading instrumentation structural limits for high-yield mining lines."
	quest.6FF8291A3D5763F2.title: "Metallurgical Upgrades: The &dIesnium Pickaxe&r"
	quest.7044EAB5EDF32BBC.quest_desc: [
		"To guarantee complete tactical oversight across a facility's high-speed assembly loops, an engineer must integrate the &9Crafting Monitor&r into the primary terminal grid."
		""
		"Once this analytical display panel is securely linked to the active network bus line, it functions as a live ledger, allowing an operative to track exactly which item IDs are currently processing within the automated manufacturing queue."
		""
		"Beyond basic visual tracking, this apparatus serves a vital defensive function across the armory floor: it stands as the mandatory mechanism required to manually abort and cancel processing operations that have stalled, suffered material shortages, or become critically glitched due to machinery failures."
		""
		"Without this control link, a bottlenecked schematic could permanently freeze a colony's automated foundries, draining power while yielding zero martial assets."
	]
	quest.70F342782B5E0997.quest_desc: [
		"Step 2: Builder"
		""
		"Before anything can be built, you need a Builder. The Builder must build their own Builder’s Hut before building any other huts, and they cannot build or upgrade a hut to a higher level than their own hut level."
		""
		"Hint: Gather as many materials as possible to give to your Builder when they start building. They will ask you for all kinds of materials for each building or upgrade, depending on the style of building you have chosen. The materials needed for most styles will be mainly wood, cobblestone, and torches for the lower levels. Further upgrades will require more elaborate materials."
		""
		"Hint: Consider upgrading the Builder’s Hut to level 2 as soon as you can so the Builder can upgrade other buildings."
		""
		"Hint: Upgrade your huts to the highest level possible (level 5 for all of them except the Tavern) to get achievements (and increase the speed at which the worker levels)."
	]
	quest.70F342782B5E0997.title: "Builder's Hut"
	quest.70FD8856BFCD9AEE.quest_desc: [
		"The absolute zenith of the spreading plague, this cataclysmic behemoth reigns as the largest and most dangerous titan among the &cRot Mobs&r. "
		""
		"It carries a staggering, near-impenetrable vitality equivalent to one hundred and sixty standard measures of health, elevating it to a catastrophic threat that strikes absolute terror into the hearts of seasoned explorers. "
		""
		"Driven by the raw, consuming hatred inherent to all infected &cRot Mobs&r, this towering horror launches into a brutal campaign to butcher the proud &2Stoneborns&r and dismantle the ancient &7Forgottens&r. "
		""
		"Should a legendary champion somehow orchestrate its definitive fall, its bursting flesh will surrender a massive bounty of precious &cUtheric Shards&r."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_rotbeast.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.70FD8856BFCD9AEE.title: "&cRotbeast&r"
	quest.70FD8C7E6CDE96DF.quest_desc: [
		"This specialized apparatus serves as your primary utility tool for securing mobile entities. It allows you to instantly siphon, store, and transport almost any living creature or hostile monster within a compact, hand-held matrix."
		""
		"Once a target is safely trapped inside, the containment unit retains its internal data footprint. You can easily carry the item across dimensions and right-click the ground elsewhere to flawlessly re-deploy the specimen at a new location. This makes it an invaluable asset for stocking your manual factory pens, populating localized mob farms, or moving specific organic catalysts directly into the center of your active possession circles."
	]
	quest.70FD8C7E6CDE96DF.quest_subtitle: "Capturing and deploying live specimens for logistical or sacrificial transport."
	quest.70FD8C7E6CDE96DF.title: "Biological Containment: &dThe Soul Gem"
	quest.7145EC3C300E7DBB.quest_subtitle: "Pray for little lag, we wish you success!"
	quest.7145EC3C300E7DBB.title: "Complete The Final Dungeon"
	quest.716FD0C8F4A7AD60.title: "Gravity Defying Gravitite"
	quest.71BFA98D54EA1BAD.quest_subtitle: "Use this powerful wand to command your pets"
	quest.71E1454990DEC451.quest_desc: [
		"The absolute zenith of malice beneath the waves, the gargantuan &bGwibs&r exist as the swollen, violently mutated sovereigns of the abyssal seas. "
		""
		"They share a lineage with the fragile &bGwiblings&r, yet they have traded all innocence for an insatiable, blinding fury. "
		""
		"Do not expect to conquer them for profit or glory; their massive, thick hides yield absolutely zero salvageable materials upon their slaughter, nor can their colossal frames be contained within a simple traveler's bucket. "
		""
		"They exist purely to punish the arrogant. To disturb their waters is to realize your own insignificance, for they offer nothing to this world but unmitigated agony."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_gwib.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.71E1454990DEC451.title: "&bGwib&r"
	quest.71EE6E6BA4C564FE.quest_desc: [
		"As your resource extraction lines scale up, the baseline cycle speeds of standard summoning and infusion matrices quickly become a significant throughput bottleneck in your factory. To eliminate this construction downtime entirely, you can channel the stabilization field of &cSevira's Permanent Confinement&r to manufacture an upgraded &bIesnium Ritual Bowl&r."
		""
		""
		"Deploying this advanced component at the exact geographic center of your pentacle in place of a standard Golden Ritual Bowl radically overhauls the matrix's energetic throughput."
		""
		"The exotic alloys within the bowl sharply accelerate the dimensional tearing process, drastically compressing the operational window of all active ceremonies down to a mere one-fourth of their original execution time. This serves as an essential upgrade for establishing rapid, high-yield automation loops in your late-game processing rooms."
	]
	quest.71EE6E6BA4C564FE.quest_subtitle: "Maximizing ceremony cycle speeds through advanced metallurgical anchors."
	quest.71EE6E6BA4C564FE.title: "Acceleration Matrix: &bIesnium Ritual Bowls&r"
	quest.72BD673DBEBD98B8.quest_desc: [
		"The foundational synthesis required within the matrix of &eEziveus' Spectral Compulsion&r is the creation of Research Fragment Dust. This refined particle compound acts as a vital magical stabilizer, bridging the gap between basic earthly materials and high-tier otherworldly components."
		""
		"Once synthesized, you must combine this dust with crushed emerald particles in a standard crafting grid to manufacture your first batch of &aLime Chalk&r. This specialized colored modifier is strictly mandatory for sketching out the complex, secondary parameters required by advanced pentacle schematics."
	]
	quest.72BD673DBEBD98B8.quest_subtitle: "Your first industrial synthesis inside the infusion matrix."
	quest.72BD673DBEBD98B8.title: "Alchemical Dusts: &bLime Chalk Components&r"
	quest.72E3BA59807C4464.quest_desc: [
		"Securing the full spectrum of colored modifiers and foundation inks marks your transition into an elite echelon of arcane engineering. With your logistics labs fully stocked, you are finally cleared to layout the pinnacle formulation of the second &dDemon-less&r discipline: &dRonaza's Contact&r. This ultimate ceremony stands as the definitive capstone matrix of the entire modpack, requiring a flawless, synchronized deployment of every geometric principle you have integrated thus far."
		""
		"By drawing raw, unfiltered energy directly from the cosmic architecture rather than filtering it through a bound spirit, the circle bypasses standard physical limits entirely. While the immense structural strain placed on the local spatial grid restricts this matrix to highly specialized, low-frequency usage, the resulting transmutations yield unparalleled endgame assets and reality-bending machinery that completely eclipse all previous technology lines."
	]
	quest.72E3BA59807C4464.quest_subtitle: "Operationalizing the complete runic spectrum for absolute reality realignment."
	quest.72E3BA59807C4464.title: "The Grand Unified Matrix: &dRonaza's Contact&r"
	quest.7327E90A53630AA8.quest_desc: [
		"Expanding upon the tool-maintenance mechanics introduced by &aStrigeor's Higher Binding&r, the advanced matrix of &cSevira's Permanent Confinement&r can be configured to execute a comprehensive item restoration loop powered by a bound Afrit entity."
		""
		"While lower-tier setups are strictly limited to scribing tools, this advanced stabilization field can handle heavy machinery and elite instrumentation. You can route depleted &eDemon Miners&r, high-tier armor matrices, and advanced harvesting tools directly into the circle to completely restore them to 100% operational durability."
		""
		"The alchemical cleansing process operates with perfect fidelity. All targeted assets retain their complete array of modifications—including custom apotheosis affixes, deep enchantments, and specialized metadata profiles—ensuring zero data loss or property degradation during the restoration cycle."
	]
	quest.7327E90A53630AA8.quest_subtitle: "Deploying high-tier fire elementals to completely reverse tool and machinery degradation."
	quest.7327E90A53630AA8.title: "Total Restoration: &cSevira's Permanent Confinement&r"
	quest.7333E2A32FC534C0.quest_desc: ["Found in Desert Pyramids."]
	quest.7333E2A32FC534C0.quest_subtitle: "Found in Desert Pyramid chests"
	quest.73862CAC8625B649.quest_desc: ["Fishing loot."]
	quest.739601B0C43B239B.quest_desc: [
		"Though their outer flesh burns with a vibrant sapphire radiance, the true secret of the Indigo Mushrooms lies locked within their bleeding spores. "
		""
		"When crushed and subjected to intense refinement, their brilliant blue pigment undergoes a drastic, unnatural transformation—yielding a pitch-black dye of absolute opacity. "
		""
		"Alchemists and weavers highly prize this fluid, as it drinks in the light and permanently stains any fabric it touches with the deep shadows of the lowlands."
	]
	quest.74448AA44DC11420.quest_subtitle: "Open 50 Containers"
	quest.744DBE831C120B2F.quest_desc: [
		"A sudden shift in the gravel can spell doom for the uninitiated, for what appears to be a dormant stone may well be a camouflaged &2Mog&r. "
		""
		"These rock-bound entities possess a bizarre, mineral-based biology that reacts uniquely to the environment. "
		""
		"Cultivators have discovered that a pair of &2Mogs&r can be enticed to propagate their species when offered a steady diet of Depthrock Pebbles. "
		""
		"Should they fall in battle, their stony carapaces fracture to reveal a harvest of raw pebbles or patches of standard Mogmoss—a highly versatile, fibrous growth utilized across a vast array of craft and alchemical recipes."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_mog.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.744DBE831C120B2F.title: "&2Mog&r"
	quest.74A7079C5088AF8D.quest_desc: ["Use your Lamp of Cinders to burn away the thorns and enter the Thornlands."]
	quest.74A7079C5088AF8D.title: "Enter the Thornlands"
	quest.74A8812364ECCF90.quest_desc: [""]
	quest.753B1F74B1AB46FF.quest_subtitle: "Countless useful relic can be found in ancient structures, guarded by powerful entities, can you collect them all?"
	quest.753B1F74B1AB46FF.title: "Remains of Better Times"
	quest.75AD0CEBC1335915.quest_desc: ["The &dReactor Controller&r is the heart of the reactor. When a reactor is formed, you can right-click the terminal to open up the reactor interface.\\n\\nDepending on if it is a &9Passively Cooled&r or an &eActively Cooled&r reactor, the interface will change. Passively Cooled reactors are used to produce power directly by burning fuel. Actively Cooled Reactors use the heat created to vaporize the coolant, which is then sent into a Turbine to create power.\\n\\nIn the interface of a passive reactor, you can see and toggle the status and waste ejection. You'll also see the temps, how much FE/t the reactor is producing, and how much fuel the reactor is burning per tick."]
	quest.75DD345164EE5CD9.quest_desc: [
		"&6High Speed Tracks&r are like &6Reinforced Tracks&r but obviously faster. They'll need &cTrack Kits&r to help build up speed though! And careful around corners."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/railcraft/rail_speed.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.7604D8B3C9FCCFD9.quest_desc: [
		"To forge the actual 'Hard Drives' that anchor a mass-digitization network, an engineer must combine structural casing with digital intelligence. "
		""
		"This is achieved by fabricating a reinforced &9Storage Housing&r and marrying it directly to a micro-engineered &6Storage Part&r at an assembly table."
		""
		"An artisan must simply craft the precise data-tier capacity required for the colony's stockpile, then slide that specialized core component into the housing frame to forge a completed &9Storage Disk&r."
		""
		"Once fully assembled, this specialized media cell functions as a stable repository, holding thousands of individual items virtually within its digitized memory matrix."
		""
		"To initialize its sorting functions, the completed cell must be physically slid into an active &9Disk Drive&r docking bay wired directly into your network bus line."
		""
		"Because these data cells are forged from exceptionally durable, blast-resistant alloys to protect your vital imperial assets, a completed Storage Disk possesses absolute structural permanence—it will never dissolve or despawn if carelessly dropped or lost into the dangerous wilds of the world."
	]
	quest.7604D8B3C9FCCFD9.quest_subtitle: "Section XVII: The Creation and Deployment of Item Storage Disks"
	quest.7604D8B3C9FCCFD9.title: "Hardware Assembly: Constructing The Media Storage Cells"
	quest.7617737FC179EA1A.quest_desc: [
		"When encased in a full suit of &bFroststeel&r Armor, a warrior commands a defensive threshold only slightly inferior to the legendary brilliance of diamond plating. "
		""
		"The dense, freezing composition of the metal anchors the wearer firmly to the earth, absorbing heavy impacts to grant immense resistance against devastating knockback attacks. "
		""
		"However, this absolute stability demands a severe physical sacrifice. "
		""
		"The biting, localized frost emanating from the plates penetrates the bones, locking the muscles into a sluggish state and inflicting a permanent reduction to movement speed. "
		""
		"It is a bulwark designed for the immovable guardian, not the swift scout."
	]
	quest.7617737FC179EA1A.title: "&bFroststeel&r Armor"
	quest.7617AC4CACC5045C.quest_desc: ["Click to be given a link to the Minecolonies wiki page. Quest only works once so save the link if you need it or use google."]
	quest.768C7CE1F3C4331F.quest_desc: [
		"Step 5: Food"
		""
		"The next major thing you need for your colony is food. The fastest way to get food is to build a Fisher’s Hut. You could build a Farmer’s Hut or one of the animal herders, but a Fisher is faster. Building a Restaurant may also be advisable if you don’t want to feed your colonists (or cook their food) by hand."
	]
	quest.76CDC18D7A208512.quest_desc: [
		"Deep within the shadowed expanse of the &2&lUndergarden&r, the vile creatures known as &cRot Mobs&r carry a insidious blight, capable of infecting travelers with the corruptive essence of &cUtherium&r. "
		""
		"When contracted in minor amounts, the body can naturally fight off the sickness, allowing the rot to slowly decay and fade over time. "
		""
		"However, should the infection reach a critical threshold, it permanently binds to the host's vitality and will never subside on its own. "
		""
		"The only known salvation lies in &3Rogdorium&r, a rare mineral found exclusively within the crushing depths of the Dreadrock regions. "
		""
		"This precious substance can be consumed directly to purge the sickness, or meticulously infused into your armor to forge a permanent ward against the blight."
	]
	quest.76CDC18D7A208512.title: "Warning"
	quest.774420C19F369850.quest_desc: [
		"Step 1: Supply Camp/Supply Ship"
		""
		"Once you have chosen a location for your colony, you must place a Supply Ship or Supply Camp. You can only place one of these per world. The Supply Camp/Ship gives you the Town Hall block you need to officially start your colony. They also have some other supplies you may need during the building of your colony. Once you have the Town Hall block and the build tool, the remaining camp/ship is just decoration. You can leave it or tear it down."
		""
		"To place the Supply Ship, you need to have a large enough body of water (at least 32 x 20). "
		""
		"When you place the Supply Ship, it will spawn a chest that will contain the Town Hall block and the build tool. Once the Supply Ship is placed, you can’t place another in the world."
		""
		"Place the Supply Ship by right-clicking the item directly on the water/ground – if you have a build tool already, don’t use it for this (you’re expected to get the tool from the ship rather than already having one)."
		""
		"Hint: If you’re not able to place the Supply Camp/Ship, try it block by block: one to the right, left, closer or further from the area you cleared. The area cannot contain any holes or have any flowers, grass, ferns, seaweed, coral etc."
	]
	quest.775D176081DD75F5.quest_desc: [
		"Right-clicking on a Turbine Controller when it is fully built will show you the Turbine Interface."
		""
		"Here, you can see all of the stats for the Turbine. "
		""
		"Hovering over each will tell you more info about each one."
		""
		"On the bottom left, you'll have 2 arrows to control the &9Flow Rate&r. "
		""
		"This controls how much heated vapor is pumped into the Turbine. "
		""
		"To know how much you should set this to, check your reactor's &dVapor Production Rate&r as a starting point."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/turbineui.png width:200 height:150 align:center}"
	]
	quest.775D176081DD75F5.title: "Turbine Interface"
	quest.785AC64B477BAC33.quest_subtitle: "Makes various Nether Materials"
	quest.787415570026FFAA.quest_desc: [
		"To maximize resource yields from raw geologic excavations, an engineer can infuse the mechanical core of a &4Destructor&r with potent arcanum modifiers. "
		""
		"Integrating these specialized enchantment matrices completely alters the unit’s demolition profile, imbuing its extraction face with properties that mirror the finest hand-carved tools."
		""
		"A premier tactical application of this advanced methodology involves creating a localized extraction loop to amplify rare mineral yields. "
		""
		"Imagine an automated mechanical Quarry or long-range Builder siphoning pristine, Silk-Touched mineral blocks directly into your central database. "
		""
		"By routing those intact deposits to a directional &bConstructor&r, the network automatically structures the raw blocks into the physical environment. "
		""
		"Immediately afterward, a paired &4Destructor&r—heavily augmented with a &eFortune Matrix Upgrade&r—shatters the positioned blocks. "
		""
		"This calculated cyclic destruction forces the ore to fracture at peak geometric efficiency, multiplying your raw resource yields far beyond the limitations of standard excavation operations."
	]
	quest.787415570026FFAA.quest_subtitle: "Section XIV: Yield Amplification via Destructor Augmentation"
	quest.787415570026FFAA.title: "Arcanum Modification: Enchantment Matrix Integration"
	quest.788138E50FC2E340.quest_desc: [
		"The &aDictionary Of Spirits&r serves as the foundational codex for &dOccultism&r. Constructing this grimoire is a strict requirement if you intend to advance through any branch of this arcane discipline."
		""
		"While this chapter provides your primary automation roadmap, the physical dictionary contains its own comprehensive, internal reference entries detailing precise geometric schematics, entity behaviors, and advanced lore."
		""
		"Beyond serving as an informative reference guide, the book itself functions as a critical material component in numerous advanced crafting recipes throughout the modpack, making its immediate fabrication mandatory for your logistical progression."
	]
	quest.788138E50FC2E340.title: "Book of &cDeeeemonsssss"
	quest.78D8F40AA9568511.quest_desc: ["The Powered Rolling Machine is much better version of the Manual Rolling Machine. \\n\\nYou don't have to keep looking in the machine to craft things and it will automatically craft all of them. \\n\\nThe only problem is it needs power!"]
	quest.79AF484CC3F00727.quest_desc: [
		"Step 8: Warehouse and courier"
		""
		"At this point, you might be tired of bringing all of the resources to the Builder and taking them from the Fisher, Forester, Miner, etc. You also might want to store items in one place. Well, the Warehouse and Courier’s Hut are the solution you are looking for! Courier transport items between the Warehouse and all of the workplaces. The Clipboard and Resource Scroll may be helpful!"
	]
	quest.79C652E3FCB88550.quest_desc: [
		"The unusual beasts known as &5Gloompers&r maintain a deceptively passive demeanor as they wander the lowlands, yet they possess a biological retaliation system that elevates them to a truly neutral status. "
		""
		"When provoked or struck by a careless blade, their skin instantly secretes a volatile mist, unleashing a localized cloud that lingers in the air much like an alchemical potion. "
		""
		"Should a hunter successfully neutralize the beast, its carcass surrenders premium leather hides and a harvest of its muscular legs—a meat celebrated across the realm for its incredibly rich, savory taste. "
		""
		"For those looking to domesticate them, a pair of &5Gloompers&r can be enticed to breed when offered a harvest of ripe Gloomgourds."
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_gloomper.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.79C652E3FCB88550.title: "&5Gloomper&r"
	quest.7A3D002083346C50.quest_desc: [
		"Before expanding your operations deeper into &dOccultism&r, you must understand how structural geometric multi-blocks scale. Advanced pentacles are explicitly designed to build directly upon the layout foundations of their predecessors."
		""
		"This backward-compatible blueprint architecture means you do not need to construct separate, individual structures for every single tier of a specific discipline. A single, high-tier summoning circle can seamlessly handle lower-tier actions as well. For example, the advanced &9Fatma's Incentivized Attraction&r layout natively incorporates the footprint of all previous &aFoliot&r and &aDjini&r summoning matrices."
		""
		"To optimize your base layout for future upgrades without needing to constantly tear down walls, it is highly recommended to dedicate four distinct 19x19 floor grids early on. Assign one perimeter block for Summoning, one for Infusion, one for Possession, and a final zone for miscellaneous (Wild and Eldritch) rituals."
	]
	quest.7A3D002083346C50.title: "Geometric Foundations: &dPentacles&r"
	quest.7A4D535DC0EDFDA8.quest_desc: [
		"Extending your logistical reach beyond your central storage laboratory requires a dedicated sub-spatial data link. You can establish remote access to your active network using either a physical &eStable Wormhole&r terminal or a portable &aStorage Accessor&r remote."
		""
		"To calibrate a &eStable Wormhole&r, shift-right-click your central &dStorage Actuator&r block to lock the terminal's frequency matrix. Once synced, you can deploy the Wormhole block anywhere else in your base to serve as an identical, instantly synchronized physical access terminal."
		""
		"Conversely, the hand-held &aStorage Accessor&r operates as a wireless remote control using the exact same shift-linking mechanic. This mobile interface bypasses traditional physical constraints, allowing you to access, store, and request resources from your network even when exploring entirely separate dimensions."
	]
	quest.7A4D535DC0EDFDA8.title: "Wireless Network Access"
	quest.7A6D9E7DAD77F895.quest_desc: ["Craft it using aquatic items."]
	quest.7B4AAC741F0A6073.quest_desc: ["Every reactor needs &9Reactor Control Rods&r and &9Fuel Rods&r. These control how fuel is inserted into the reactor.\\n\\nThe Control Rods are placed on the top face of the reactor. You can also have more than one per reactor, but you must have at least 1. Typically, the more you have, the more fuel the reactor can use and burn. That can mean more overall power, but at the cost of higher burn rates, depending on the setup of your reactor.\\n\\nFor every Control Rod, you'll need enough Fuel Rods to extend to the base of the reactor. For example, if your reactor is 5 blocks tall, you'll need 3 Fuel Rods extending from each Control Rod.\\n\\nIf you right-click on a Control Rod, you can control how much fuel is burned in the reactor by inserting or retracting the fuel rods. The further that you extend the rods, the less fuel that will be burned."]
	quest.7B4AAC741F0A6073.title: "Reactor Control Rods"
	quest.7BB9B1E8888BA04F.quest_desc: ["Found in Nether Fortresses."]
	quest.7BB9B1E8888BA04F.quest_subtitle: "Found in Nether Fortress chests"
	quest.7C4D8AA107780795.quest_desc: [
		"By using the &aFluidizer&r, we can combine &dBlutonium&r with &eYellorium&r to make &2Verderium."
		""
		"When used as fuel in a reactor, &2Verderium&r produces &cRossinite&r as a reactant. We need this!"
		""
		"To use &2Verderium&r as a fuel, you'll need to make &cFuel Injection Ports&r for your reactor."
		""
		"Note: You might need to empty out the fuel currently in your reactor, or make a new reactor for this purpose. "
	]
	quest.7C4E4793DA887DE4.quest_desc: ["Based off of the original mod &eBig Reactors&r, &aExtreme Reactors&r allows you to build customizable multiblock Reactors!\\n\\nThe main element is of course, Uranium. You'll need this and a lot of coal and iron to get building.\\n\\nIf you're ever lost along the way, refer to &aThe Extreme Book&r for help! "]
	quest.7C4E4793DA887DE4.title: "Welcome to &9Extreme Reactors&r!"
	quest.7C9CB235D52BFE01.quest_desc: ["This place seems to have it's own set of tools, although your current ones should still do their job, somewhat."]
	quest.7C9CB235D52BFE01.quest_subtitle: "New Stone? New Wood? Punch the Tree!"
	quest.7C9CB235D52BFE01.title: "That shade of green drives me crazy"
	quest.7CDA9D29A9BC04B1.title: "Find a Snowy Forest"
	quest.7D40B80DBBC4E160.quest_desc: ["The Manual Rolling Machine will be your little crafting machine for many things material for railcraft! \\n\\nWhen you put the recipe in and it can make more than 1 it will autocraft while you're still looking at it. When you leave the Rolling Machine while crafting it will abort the crafting and put it in your inventory. \\n\\nYou must manually build the last recipe!"]
	quest.7E010951FA8E6F84.quest_subtitle: "Obtain ALL the fabled rare moa eggs!"
	quest.7E010951FA8E6F84.title: "The ultimate challenge"
	quest.7E07C5A6FA6B6B1F.quest_desc: [
		"Once you've built a fully functional &aReprocessor&r, you can pump in power, water, and &9Cyanite&r to create &dBlutonium&r."
		""
		"This can be used as a fuel for your reactor, and creates its own waste called &9Magentite&r. "
	]
	quest.7E3DA4168D352B42.quest_desc: [
		"At first glance, these mushrooms appear ordinary. "
		""
		"Their true secret, however, lies in what they produce: \\n\\nVeils! "
		""
		"They make for an incredibly useful decoration block."
		""
		""
		"{image:ftb_quests:textures/gui/ftb_quests/images/undergarden_veil.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.7E3DA4168D352B42.title: "Veil Mushroom Bog"
	quest.7F187E291C3D5BA7.quest_desc: ["The Fluid Unloader is the exact opposite of the Fluid Loader. Instead of being over the &6Track&r its under. Instead of giving &3Steam Locomotives&r water it takes their water. I don't know why you'd want to do that but you can!"]
	quest.7F4B734CFB0F0306.quest_desc: ["These new &7Carts&r are similar to the special &2Vanilla&r &7Carts&r. The &7Minecart with a Tank&r will hold and move any Liquid held in it. The &7Minecart with an Energy cell&r will instead hold and move Energy!"]
	quest.7FA85713C86166DA.quest_desc: [
		"To maintain total strategic dominion over a fortress's industrial output while conducting active field operations, an officer must carry the specialized &9Wireless Crafting Monitor&r."
		""
		"This advanced, hand-held tracking module syncs effortlessly with the atmosphere's data frequencies, allowing you to access your network crafting queue wirelessly from anywhere across the battlements."
		""
		"By projecting the live assembly lines directly onto a portable screen, it grants a traveling engineer the vital capability to monitor ongoing munitions manufacturing or remotely abort glitched processing routines without sprinting back to the central forge hub."
	]
	quest.7FA85713C86166DA.quest_subtitle: "Section XXVIII: The Wireless Crafting Monitor"
	quest.7FA85713C86166DA.title: "Signal Reception: Remote Pipeline Access"
	quest.7FBD6FCE3ECF0921.quest_desc: [
		"As your production lines scale, relying on the constant manual consumption of volatile &cDemon's Dream Fruit&r to maintain a fleeting &7Third Eye&r status effect quickly becomes a major bottleneck in your operations."
		""
		"To completely automate your spatial awareness, you must manufacture the &dOtherworld Goggles&r. When equipped—either in a standard armor head slot or nestled directly inside your Curios jewelry matrix—this visor emits a constant, passive resonance field. This grants you permanent, uninterrupted vision into the hidden layers of reality, letting you harvest resources seamlessly without any down-time or dietary requirements."
	]
	quest.7FBD6FCE3ECF0921.quest_subtitle: "Bypassing dietary consumption for permanent extra-dimensional vision."
	quest.7FBD6FCE3ECF0921.title: "Permanent Clarity: &dOtherworld Goggles&r"
	quest.7FC7DC38E9E5741E.quest_desc: [
		"The utility of these extra-dimensional entities extends far beyond mere ore pulverization."
		""
		"The mod features a robust array of specialized spirits capable of managing entire automated logistical networks—including dedicated transportation thralls to transfer items between containers, tireless lumberjacks to clear timber grids, and precise sorting agents."
		""
		""
		"Additionally, you can channel your resources into manifesting &dFamiliars&r. These minor helper entities follow you throughout your journey, providing powerful passive stat buffs, carrying mobile storage inventories, or actively engaging hostile entities in combat. Consult the dedicated &dFamiliar Rituals&r tab inside your guidebook to evaluate the unique mechanical traits of each available companion."
	]
	quest.7FC7DC38E9E5741E.title: "My &dFamiliars&r"
